[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Super tasty food. Value for money. Keep it up. We ordered chicken tried rice, paneer fried rice n gobhi Manchurian. It was yummmm. Will surely look forward to order from here next time'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This is a new outlet opened inside Prasanthi complex at Channasandra. So we decided to taste the food for a dinner.
It's a small outlet like others inside the complex with 10 people seating arrangement and all outside seating.

The menu was having lot of dishes specially in non veg dishes and also parathas.
As we packed the food for us the food preparation time was quick.
The staff were humble and were ready to manage slight modifications.

We ordered 4 tandoori rotis ,one chicken gravy and one chilli chicken dry.
The chicken gravy was good in taste with finely sliced onion and garlic with 4 good pieces of chicken.
The chill chicken was also nice with nicely coated chicken pieces and onion & peppers. It was having a good sweet and sour taste.
Some of the tandoori rotis were not cooked properly , I think it was removed from the tandoor too early.

With a very good price tag and tasty food it is recommended...")]

column2: Thigalarapalya, Hoodi, Kadugodi Plantation, Whitefield, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  No delevary my order'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Hi,
As for ages, pizza is a great option for home delivery and the same is true for me.
Recently I placed an order on this joint for one veg Hawaain pizza and one non veg pizza. Disappointed with non availability of Hawaain pizza, as after confirmation of order, restaurant called and asked for substitute topping instead of Pineapple. As Hawaain is not the same in absence of key ingredient.

Taste wise it was OK, but lack of cheese was bit of turn off and even the thin crust was not up to the mark.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  We sampled a simple sausage pizza. The crust is very thin and cook superbly, thanks in part to know-who from the pizza tosser and the hot coal oven they cook it in. The pizza has a distinct taste and the flavors mingle well with each other, especially the fresh cut basil sprinkled on when the pizza emerges from the oven.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I've been to Dominos, Crunch and Pizza hut in the last month and I have to say that I liked the crust at Crunch the best. At dominos it was actually a little soggy. Even at pizza hut, it was a bit soggy. But at Crunch it was definitely not soggy and the crust was yummy."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Crunch hit the spot - perfectly crispy, charred crust, with a delicious and appropriate amount of sweet San Marzano tomato sauce, fresh mozzarella and basil. The other half of the pizza had  wild mushrooms, but I have to say the Babe's Demise is the BOMB!!! Will be back...."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  One of the original pizza places. Worth the wait. Delicious crispy pizza with amazing toppings (free fresh garlic and yummy meatballs and pepperoni) at not-so-exhorbitant prices. I dream about it.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Not only the best pizza in bangalore City,also outstanding service! You must try the fresh mozzarella slice...simply delicious!
will surely be ordering from here again'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I used Crunch for catering for an event and they were incredibly helpful. I worked with manager jitin, who was amazing. He was very accommodating and professional. I would absolutely use them again - the pizza arrived as scheduled (two deliveries) and was beautiful and delicious.

The pizza itself is fantastic. I still prefer it in a crispy slice compared to the full pizza, but the pizzas are so good. Definitely the best pizza in the area - you won't find anything that will top it."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Oh Crunch: it's really going to be a problem that I live so close to this great old-school pizza place. 

It's a no-frills, simple, delicious pizza place that feels like you stepped back in time. The plain cheese pizza is pretty average, but cough up a couple bucks more and splurge on the other pizzas or the fresh mozzarella. Both are absolutely delicious!"), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I'd be lying if I said it wasn't conveniently located and lets face it, pizza is generally one of the few cheap pleasures in this city so its often a no brainer, but the real reason is that they deliver very fast indeed. Its also worth mentioning that the staff is always really friendly and upbeat, which is rare and certainly unexpected for a pizza joint--especially one that is as busy as Crunch."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I always try Biriyani here its good taste was good and nice place to spend time and nice atmosphere everything k definitely we can visit again'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Anilkumar
DJ Kumar Mighty Marvel Apartment Bangalore Karnataka kannamangala yes anilkumar Saurabh Kundla 1 live Mighty Marwal Zomato booking Anil Kumar'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This outlet is located inside the Prasanthi complex at Channasandra.
It's completely outdoor seating so in a rainy day it will be quite difficult to dine out.
Service is okay and staff not that great.
But the food was good with nice flavours...we ordered one chicken briyani and one chicken combo .
The chicken briyani was having good quantity of rice , 2 pieces of good size chicken and one half egg. The rice quality was very good and was having nice flavours and to the price tag of 130 RS it's really good.
The chicken combo was having 3 rotis ,chicken curry and salad.
The rotis we're soft and of good size whereas the chicken curry was also nice in taste with 3 pieces of chicken and a nice gravy. Although oil was bit high in the curry and literally we have to throw the oil above the curry. But the gravy was having good amount of onions and garlic which made it flavourful and gave a good aroma.

Overall nice food but ambience has to be increased a bit ."), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  Situated in Prashanti Complex, Channasandra Main Road, Near Bus Stop. This place provides best biryani. I have tried their Chicken Dum Biryani, it had 2 pieces of chicken and half boiled egg. The quantity of rice is more than enough for a single p@erson and the size of chicken piece is also good. They serve biryani along with raita and gravy. For the cost of Rs 140, it is more than what we can expect. They have a nice seating arrangement.
Rating :
Food : 3.5/5
Seating Arrangement : 3.5/5
Overall Rating : 3.5/5
Keep up the good work.
Happy Eating.
Hyderabadi Dum Biryani'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED

I have ordered masala papad, tomato soup, sweetcorn soup, chilli gobi, garlic naan, kadhai veg & masala dosa.They need to give emphasis on revamping their recipes so that taste can be enhanced. This was going to be my first & last visit here.

ambrosiia.com'), ('Rated 2.5', 'RATED
  A good place. Average food. Chat and North Indian food are average. South Indian food might not be as good.

If you want to visit, the only thing worth visiting is the ambience. You get ice gola and loads of dance happening. The place has a village vibe with the waiters wearing Rajasthani costume. The folks here are pretty friendly. The ice gola will take you back by a few years.

Will I visit again? Not sure.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The best food for the best price , cleanliness is not up to the mark but the service is great with this guys and the taste for sure will call you back'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Used to go there when I was living near Hoodi. Taste and quality of food is very good here. Every penny you pay for is worth for what they serve. The Staff here are very friendly. They don't have much items in their menu but whatever they serve is very good. Especially chicken briyani. Compared to the restaurants that charge more and serve some tasteless food, this restaurant is truly a value for money restaurant. They just need to improve on hygiene side a little bit. Overall it is a Cheap and best restaurant for people who are living on a low budget. :)")]

column2: 2nd Floor, Food Court, Phoenix Market City Mall, Whitefield, Bangalore
column11: Vegetable Biryani, Non Veg Thali, Plain Rice, Chicken Pot Biryani, Naan
column14: [('Rated 3.0', "RATED\n  Located in the food court of Phoenix Market City, this place is known for its various biryani choices. I've had the mutton biryani from here a few times and it is always satisfying. Quite a large portion served in a traditional clay pot that never seems to run out of rice. Decent amount of meat pieces on the bone how I like it. Very good flavour too. My only issue is the raita. I don't understand why so many restaurants give this watery liquid which vaguely resembles a kind of raita. It is more like water with a tiny bit of curd. This is not raita! Especially when we are paying around 300rs we should get a proper raita. Apart from that, I like to visit this place when I need to recharge from intense shopping! Friendly staff too.")]

  I tried the king of all parathas- the aloo paratha here. It amount of stuffing was great. The paratha was served with some mix-veg raita, pickle and salad. From its looks, the paratha seemed as if it was baked in an oven or microwave. It was tasty and filling.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Everything from paranthas to dal Makhani to chole nd the curd is pretty nice only disappointing thing was the cheap quality plates they use . A must go place for all the parantha lovers in bangalore'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This is really good for paratha lovers.It offers plenty of types of parathas of good quality.I ordered one alu gobi paratha meal. The paratha was nice crispy and the fillings was really good.Served with dal makhni,delhi chole and chaas.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This place has a wide variety of amazing parathas. A must go to place when you visit the food court at Inorbit mall. Though the food court at Inorbit mall needs to be managed properly. It is usually empty and the staff seems uninterested to serve.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Located in the food court of Inorbit Mall, Whitefield, it's a decent enough place if you like parathas. 200 for a paratha might look like very expensive at the first glance but actually it's served with Dal Makhni, Punjabi Chhole Masala, Raitha, Onion Pickle and Drink of the day. I went here yesterday again. I've been here a couple of times and it is my first choice if I ever have to dine at Inorbit food court. The parathas are quite tasty probably because of the fact that they're made in "desi ghee".

A must try place if you're at Inorbit Mall.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  The name says only partahas but they serve parathas which are good for nothing--improper filling and not cooked properly. The oil they use is definitely the worst quality oil as it smells like hell.

Also tried their chola bhatura, could learly sense that the chhola was 2 days old--it was black in color and was so oily and spicy..advise heart patients to stay away. Their employees were wearing filthy clothes and hawai chappals-can you believe this !!

Disgusting food. Thankfully I had awesome paani puri at kailash parbat after that which made us feel better.

Only parathas should be avoided at all costs to safeguard your health'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I like thr thick heavy paratathas n chat also OK OK... Again ok option during lunch hrz bt nothing special as it is part of food court...'), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  You will find this in the food court of Inorbit mall.

The regular food is not that great and found some stones in the pulao that I ordered, so be careful of it. I returned it back and got a refund.

Although the food is not upto the "Mark", The chats are "fresh" and is tasty, you can definitely try a couple of chats here. Rest of the menu is just about average, nothing to boast about.

Ambiance: 2/5 its a mall so nothing specific.
Value for money: Nothing great, just average 3/5
Taste: Chats are good. so 3/5
Service: Not bad for a small sized outlet 3/5

Overall, Nothing much but chats are recommended IF you are hungry ONLY !!

Cheers,'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Another attempt of a joint on the Punjabi cuisine and the parathas as a quick bites, though the outlet also serves some quick chaat and chole bhature items.

Tried a couple of their Paranthas(Aloo Paneer Paranthas, Gobi Parantha etc) and some Chole Bhatures.
The Paranthas were not up to the mark with less filling and void of any great flavours, the Chole Bhature was however good and decent.'), ('Rated 2.5', "RATED
  If you want to eat authentic Chole Bhature (Delhi/Punjab style), this is the place to go to. I don't think any other restaurant makes Chole (Delhi style) as good as this guy in Bangalore. Most combos on offer will cost you Rs. 150 - 200. The serving size is really huge, so go with a very good appetite. Don't try the paranthas...they suck big time.

If you are Chole Bhature worshiper like me, don't give it a miss!")]

The ambiance is not good but the food will make u forget that...

Name the food and the chef will make that for you..'), ('Rated 2.5', 'RATED
  The Royal Darbar, what's in a name? Does this" rose" smells just as sweet? Had to go there as its just a few steps from my place.
On entering my gut feeling was to retreat, but again let food speak for itself!
Puneesh, the young college going teen was behind the counter, well spoken and mannered,took our take away Order because having you're lunch there??????

Asked for Jeera rice, Methi aloo, Dal fry with ghee and phulkas. Quantity and taste was nice but the hygiene, cleanliness get up, upkeep boy so much to be desired?')]

column2: 3rd Floor, The Forum Neighborhood Mall, Whitefield, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I had a good dining experience althought the portion size was big. Shashi who was serving my table was patient and helpful and assisted with the food choices.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I am not convinced with the desi style pizza. Looks good and interesting. They have some good choices but when tried, I felt it is not desi in taste and definitely not a pizza. Not a great experience for me atleast. One thing that attracted me is the oven there :) It looks beautiful'), ('Rated 2.5', 'RATED
  We were in Forum Value Mall recently, and decided to have lunch at The Eatery in the food court. The experience, sadly, turned out to be highly disappointing.

We were delighted to see lots of wraps, varieties of Maggi noodles and naan pizzas on the menu. The place seems to have good options for both vegetarians and non-vegetarians, but we were told none of the Maggi varieties were available then.

We opted for a Texas BBQ Paneer & Cheese naan pizza, which was extremely bland and tasteless. The pizza sauce, the paneer, the cheese, nothing had any flavour to it. The taste of the pizza needs a big-time overhaul.

The basil lemonade that we got on a complimentary basis with the naan pizza was nice, though.

At INR 300, I think the 11" naan pizza was a bit expensive. It wasn't really filling for 2 people.

The staff was friendly and courteous - no complaints on that front.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The eatery in the forum mall is a decent place serving naans masquerading as pizzas. The food is definitely delicious but prices are on the higher side. They would probably do better business if they price the naans at 150.
Ambience 3/5
Service 4/5
Taste 5/5
Value for money 3/5'), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  Visited for lunch and ordered lamb burger :2nd week of November.
It was an average burger , which is in the league of MacDonald or KFC. The ingredients used were of better quality but bun was cold and dry. They must use better quality buns .
Service was friendly and good .'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The food is freshly cooked and the place is hygienic. This is a good place to have wraps which feel lighter. Serves both veg and non veg. However the rice combo that I ordered for lacked some side like a gravy which you would crave for. The only option tomato sauce. There is only one drink that is basil lemonade again only available with combos and not on its own. You will have to stick with some soft drinks otherwise. This can really do well as food is fresh given there is a slight variation to menu which they have informed will be launched soon'), ('Rated 4.5', 'RATED
  Jus loved the texas bbq paneer and cheese naanza ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9dÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¤ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9dÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¤

The taste was delicious .....Wat else does a pizza lover need ?

Check out ths place if smday ua visiting forum neighbourhood mall .'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I had been here for lunch twice. As this place is near to my office(sigma tech park) most of the time we have lunch here. This cafe is inside the food court. Food is freshly prepared and worth the money paid. This place prepares delicious desi-pizza with Naan base, you have to try Naanz which is the typical food they prepare. Wraps are good too. Overall its a nice place to have good food at affordable price.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The eatery is a good place to have fresh food, they have limited menu but they make really good sharawarma and Amazing pizza, roles.

I have sent their kitchen and it's really clean, you will feel good after you have eaten here. The only disadvantage is that it is situated in the food court and they do not have table service

My verdict: if you are in forum neighbourhood mall and wanna have some good pizza and rolls then this is the place to be. And you will feel lite and good"), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Horrible horrible horrible..
Just can't see how these people do business.

Really sad to be at a place like this with no professionalism at all."), ('Rated 2.5', 'RATED
  I ordered for two non veg wraps.. However, I received one veg wrap and a non veg wrap.. Apart from that the wrap was pretty decent.. But they should be more careful about fulfilling the correct order..'), ('Rated 4.5', "RATED
  Was hesitant at first about ordering here, but the young cashier cum manager changed my mind and convinced me.
I ordered the sheekh naanza and enjoyed every bite of it. The crisp naan created a good base that won't go soggy with food on it. The sheekh had a good flavour of coriander to it. A very generous helping of cheese to top it all and my stomach was satisfied with what I had devoured.
Keep up the good effort in providing good food to eat.
Slightly on the pricey side (by about 15%) and a tad bit more of chicken will do the trick to get you a full 5 ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â°ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x8cÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9f rating from my side.
Looking forward to eating here again."), ('Rated 4.5', 'RATED
  We always look out for new places opening up in our neighborhood Forum mall, so when we saw the Eatery, we promptly ordered from there.
Lamb shawarma wrap - For beginners we decided to try only the shawarma and we were pleasantly surprised at how good it was! The pita was soft, warm and beautifully cooked. I did see them taking out frozen ones and then using them, but it was surprisingly good. The filling had the right quantity of sauce that tasted like tahini sauce, very generous quantities of veggies and very well flavored and cooked lamb seekh in it. I loved it. Will definitely go back to try the other things on the menu.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Food Court restaurants are handicapped by staff, individuality, costs and space?? Eatery appeared to be missing out on staff because the Counter guy was doubling as sous chef to the Cook.

Played safe and ordered chicken aromatic rice which had 3 minuscule pieces of chicken.

The Roll was just okay-came cold.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Its been a very nice experience.. superb hygenic and tasty food.. would like to visit frequently..!! And would also suggest my friends and food lovers to atleast visit this place once for a gud experience..'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I had a wish to try a different kind of pizza someday. Naanza's, my first reaction was why they name it like this. But the boy at counter told that this is a kind of healthy pizza. Therefore, I skipped the well know pizza joints in same food court. I ordered baby corn naanza's as I am not big fan of non-veg pizza.Naaza was really good. I guess it was prepared on mint sauce base instead of traditional tomato sauce. Oh! I forgot to mention that there tag line says that be un-traditional. They have really given a nice Indian twist to traditional Italian pizza. I really liked the naan base which became really crisp once it was cooked with cheese and other toppings. I think they cooked on some kind of grill pan as I could see nice grill marks on the back of naan base. But still there are some areas of improvement. I feel they could have cooked onions little bit more. But this is not a deal breaker. Kudos to the whole team. I will definitely try there other items next time."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  When you go to a food court now a days, you're either in a mood for the usual (Chinese, north Indian, Italian and south Indian). These guys mix everything up!!
Their nanza is a really nice concept that shows consistency and tastes different for every variation you order.
Their shawarma is pure Bliss! Comfort food I tell you.
It comes in a naan which is something I've not had before.
Price is OK, I guess having a kitchen in a mall is meant to increase pricing slightly but yes it is slightly high.
Do try their burgers if you'd like to sin!

Cheers.")]

column2: Food Court 2, Concourse Tech Park Mall, ITPL, Whitefield, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  I usually love Kerala food because of it's amazing taste in both vegetarian and non vegetarian dishes,in fact Kerala is also called as land of spices. But this restaurant has disappointed me ,it's not just worth the price and even I did not find it that clean.
Had been here with my teammates for lunch and we had ordered kothu parota which was really depressing . The prawn one was really spicy with no taste and quantity was less it costed 160 bucks with hardly 2 prawns cut into really tiny pieces. The chicken one was also nothing great."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Lovely food here.
Lovely taste.
Kind and generous people.

Quality and quantity is too good.

Never before did I realise that Kerala foods can be this tasty in restaurants. Have loved eating every variety these people serve.')]

I have ordered chicken friend rice, chicken manchurian, egg bhurji, tandoori chicken, Indian breads and paneer tikka masala. Chicken fried rice was totally blend. Chicken manchurian was average. Egg bhurji was very nice. Tandoori chicken was superb. Paneer tikka masala was poor.

column2: Hoodi Circle, Whitefield, Bangalore
Chicka Thirupathi Road, Channasandra, Whitefield, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 4.5', "RATED
  Lovely place.Its more of a small takeaway outlet. You can also sit and eat there but the space is small.Only 5-6 persons can eat at a time.
Coming to the chicken,it's juicy. Tender meat which thick coating is all you want in your life when you have cravings for eating chicken.
They essentially have two varieties of chicken.One comes with sprinkled chilly salt powder.Both of them are very juicy.Second one is for the people who like it a little spicy.
From wings to breast piece to leg piece you get everything.This is place certainly is worth the money. I would say it as a big competitor to the quality of chicken provided by KFC."), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  Pathetic food, Crispy chicken was not crispy and looks like they use low quality oil which adds to the misery. Ordered through Swiggy and had to throw most of the stuff. Chicken was not well cooked as well.
Overall a forgettable experience, pls avoid food from here.')]

column14:
[('Rated 1.5', 'RATED
  Not a good choice, we ordered food(ChkB) on 13-sep-16, it is mix of both  Basmathi & Normal rice, leads to a very bad taste. Even the chicken not boiled properly. Very Bad experience with this restaurant food.'), ('Rated 4.5', 'RATED
  I have to stay with my Friend nearby this place for couple of days. This small takeaway attracted me to be a bit unique and tried.  Came from Hyderabad so looking for decent Biryani. Chicken and Mutton Biryani(Only Sunday) was excellent. No colors and tasted like Hyderabad local biryani smell came. Good smell of spices also. Quantity, Hygiene and Tasty. My friend also liked it and will repeat from next time.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Ordered chicken biryani. Very average , not having any specific taste. Rice is bit overcooked , but chicken was nice. Let down is not having that aroma or smell good factor. Big plus is quantity. But Biryani lovers won't recommend this place."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered online. 

The customer service is very good - they kept me updated that the delivery might be delayed a little, though came pretty much within range.

I opted for chicken biriyani regular and kebabs. 
Briyani was okay. The chicken piece was really really small :-( . I expected at least one decent portioned chicken piece for the regular size !

Kebabs were okay, a bit oily though. But tasted fine.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Just another shop near my house, offering same boring menu of Chicken Biryani and kebabs. I ordered once from here and the kebabs were too much oily. Not recommended'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  After a very long time i had a real good biryani in Bangalore after having in so many places .  Both the Taste and Quantity where extraordinarily outstanding . The spice they put in biryani is according to our wish .I highly recommend this place for people who love biryani. For people who don't love biryani  , well once have a taste of this and  you will love it."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Had such good Biryani after a long time. By the aroma of the biryani only you can say that it will taste good. Quantity was also very good. One large Chicken Biryani (180rs) is sufficient for two person. The spices were simple , not too spicy. Heart warming hospitality of the staff. Overall it was good experience with good food.
Must try.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  I ordered biryani (one chicken and one veg) from this place just to try something other than Thindipotha.. But one of the worst biryani I have ever had in my life.   Ordered Palak Paneer, Tawa sabji and dum Aloo for home delivery. The total amount was 305. But after the food was delivered it showed 340. The price of the items on bill was high. Food taste was OK OK . dum Aloo wasn't good. Paneer and Tawa sabji was eatable. Disappointed with pricing as I saw low rates and ordered for COD."), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  Siddharth is a small, vegetarian restaurant serving North Indian dishes. The thali served is good enough to satiate your hunger. There is little difference between the taste of the gravies of paneer butter masala, veg kadai, mix veg, etc. That said, the taste is peculiar and tasty which makes me come here often on weekends. The paneer roll is a must try here as it is magnanimously loaded with paneer, spices, onions and chilies. During evenings, the place serves hot samosas and jalebis (typical North Indian style). The place should put more efforts to come to limelight as there is a huge potential to grow with mostly IT public residing in the nearby localities. My ratings go as follows:
Taste: 3/5
Ambiance:3/5
Value for money:4/5
Service:3/5'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  As the name of the restaurant goes, i was here wid my friends to hangout!! Since this was new restaurant in the neighbourhood i tried to be on the safe side by ordering regular starters that being chicken lollipops and pan fried momos after that i had kadai chicken and pepper chicken. And to my amazement they had nailed it. They were well cooked , chicken was tender from the inside, and in case of lollippps meat was juicy. Pan fried momos had sufficient filling , the right amount to satisfy your crave. This inspired me to take a little more risk, so i went with an spring roll. And you guys will think that they ought to be oily like many other restaurant s but no that was not the case here , the spring rolls were very light and had the right flavour. I guess my first visit was quite good. And my experience suggests this is a place for friends/colleagues to hang out.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED

  I would say its ok. Not good, not bad the food was just ok. But i feel its a bit overpriced. I had chole bhature and it tasted like it doesnt contain any spices.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Ambience- Located inside food court which is very spacious.

Pocket friendly- A bit costly for the quality served.

Food- Chats here are costly. You get a platter of chats where you get Pani puri, Dahi puri, Bhel puri and Sev puri. Pani puri was mediocre with the water having some wierd smell.

Dahi puri and Sev puri were gud. Bhel puri lacked the tangy tamarind flavour and did not contain peanuts or dal or tomatoes and cucumbers as one would expect in it.

Tea quantity was huge but again is was average.

Service- Prompt and quick.

Rating- 2.5 as the taste is not distinguishable.'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Located in the food court of Inorbit mall I thought of giving this place a try. I tried chaat combo which was on a sweeter side. I don't like my chaats to be sweet. Also bread pakoda we ordered was damm oily. I would never visit this place again."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Tried their special veg thali this weekend ..it was a one complete meal with dessert and buttermilk.. The food was Fresh and Tasty..the gulab jamun was awesome..'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

Try their signature dish, Kashmiri Pakora - I m loved with the dish. Best one in the menu i will with out doubt will claim. Fillings are pretty good.

  FYI to All for below concern: the concerned person called ,apologized and promised for better quality to serve to customers. So, on this note , gave another chance to do better.

Hi Authority,

I want Hotel Management to take action on this vendor , else i will take it to Food Inspection Team Of Govt. Of India.
I had visited this Vendor(Kailash ParBat) on 20-02-2017 near around 9 PM with my full family.

I had to vomit at home after taking a single bite of Thali - Mini Combo - Rs 160 and i completely left out complete food there only.

This leads to food poisioning and i could feel better only after 4 hours at home.It lead to severe repurcussions to me .
Take an  action asap , which teach these kinds of vendors , else they will keep paying with people health and wealth.       

You must inform after doing the needful for above, else I will contact the Govt. departments to investigate it very soon.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

  It has been nearly 5 years ago , I has visited their Pune outlet. And now I chanced upon this outlet while on the shopping walk at Inorbit mall few days ago. 

I always felt that they serve average food and the experience here for us was no different. Raj Kachori and chat are decent here though.

I feel there are much more better options available now and this can be easily skipped without any further thought.

  The bad:
Horrible Parathas - a thick layer of roti (inedible) with hardly any filling!
Semi-cooked rice!
Do not try Ras-malai - water instead of thick boiled milk!

The good/ decent:
Roti - was decent'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  If you are looking for value for money then this is NOT the place to go to. Usually places that charge exorbitant prices for the usual food items offer food of superior quality! But that is not the case here at Kailash Parbat. This is my second such experience. The veg Thali came at a high price ( of course!) But quantity wise it was decent. The food definitely looks good but it fails to blow your mind in terms of taste.
The rice that came with the combo was extremely bland. It felt like they just mixed vegetables and cooked rice for the heck of it! The saving grace of the whole meal was the dal and the Boondi raita. The Chana and Paneer weren't impressive either. The size of the gulab jamun that came in this meal was the size of a pebble.
The only other refreshing part of the meal was the buttermilk. Nice consistency and satisfactory taste.

Paisa Vasool? Not really."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Well, I have been to this outlet many times for lunch and dinner. The food is quute good and the quantity is also nice. Parantha's are really good at this place and I have tried mostly all paranthas available.

Today I tried Chole Bhature here. It was not the best what i have had but certainly good enough in bangalore.
Another good thing was the onion in vinegar, we usually dnt get that in bangalore .

I like the food here. Will visit again."), ('Rated 1.5', 'RATED
  Have been here. If I compare it with the outlet in Phoenix mall- this place is maybe smaller. Not as busy as the one in Phoenix mall. The food is comparatively okay. The crowd may have something to do with the foot fall in inorbit mall too. But I like this fact and prefer inorbit as compared to the crowded Phoenix.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED

  It's a no frills restaurant with no fancy decor or anything. It is just a place to get a tasty meal at a very reasonable amount. Serving home made food to many college students (as it is situated opposite MVJ college) the have everything you might want to eat as a part of your day to day meal.
The price is spot on... Not much heavy on the pocket and the quantity served is value for money.

Quick service is another important thing to note about this place. However I guess the seating arrangements can be made better and there is always room for improvement as far as the menu is concerned.

Overall, a good experience and surely recommended in case it is the end of the month, and you are looking for a good meal at a reasonable price.")]

  Worst quilty food received . I ordered kadhae paneer from this restaurant. gravy is very bad . I also received too much onion band capsicum. Don't order from this restaurant.Zomatomer care also not giving my refund."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Great Experience, Home made food, Chole bhature has good taste, kadaii paneer is highly recommendable.

Less oily, hygienic.
chawal ki kheer is awesome.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Love the food from this place. First important part, you will be eating your food from a Veg only restaurant. Have a variety of food options and I would recommend you to try Masala Veg khichdi and Mushroom masala. I ordered food from this place but there is an option for you to dine in as well. The portion while ordering might be confusing but 500 Ml is a medium box and once you order, the measured number will be written on the bottom of the container for your reference. However, restaurant gives you a good portion and quality of the food is reputable.

Thank you Desi Khana for the delicious food!')]

column14:
[('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  U.P. Dhaba, Whitefield, Bangalore
.
I ordered the following from this place:
- Kadhai Paneer
- 2 pieces Tandoori Roti
.
The paneer gravy was pathetic and the gravy was nothing like that of a kadhai paneer.
.
It was really a very disappointing experience.
.
With Love
Thetechnifoodie'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Just out of curiosity to explore, I recently visited U.P. Dhaba with my colleagues.
The food is strictly average. It's not that great, not too bad also.
We tried out the following dishes:

* Boneless Chicken Biriyani
* Pepper Chicken
* Kadai Chicken
* Kadai Paneer
* Naan

We noticed that the salt was less for the all dishes we tasted. Pepper chicken was the best among all.

Food : 3/5
Ambience : 3/5
Parking : 2/5
Service : 3/5
Cleanliness: 3/5

Rating : 2.8/5"), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  The place is not good, quality wise, they serve paneer parathas, but without paneer and they claim they are selling paneer parathas. Worst experience with them.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  Review basis online delivery...
Ordered ghee roast chicken, two butter tandoori rotis, 1 missi Roti and mango lassi.

Everything was pathetic, Chicken gravy was uncooked, I felt raw masala taste while eating the curry, it was watery and full of red chilli pepper and turmeric...
Rotis were not buttered but plain rotis. Mango lassi had nothing to do with mango's at all. It was like yellow colored sweet milky drink.

Don't order from here guys.. You will loose both your money as well as appetite."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I ordered paneer thali and baby corn manchurian.
Paneer thali had so many items that I couldn't finish them all.
Baby corn manchurian could have been more crisper but still good in taste.
Gravy items in thali were nice in taste
Gulabjamun was soft and tasty.
Mango lassi was also good
I would recommend this place for home made food lovers."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Having a sweet tooth, I get really very angry and disappointed when someone grabs sweets from my plate. I ordered a paneer meal today. Taste was average and quantity was good. Fast service too. Roti was packed in plastic pouch, came sticky and had rice grains stuck on it. Sweet and papad were mentioned in the menu but couldn't find in the pack. Highly disappointing.   You're looking at the average rating of this place and wondering if you should order? Are you in the mood for a delicious bowl of biryani? Then, yes. It's a complete, wholesome meal witha unique taste. They seem to cook the chicken and biryani separately. The chicken is decent, although I wish they had a boneless option and the quantity and sides are decent. It's definitely worth a try, despite the average rating. Trust a level 9 reviewer, and do read my reviews to know what food you should trust.

  Always stealing five rs by not giving change. Terrible behavior by staff after owner leaves. The worst coffee I ever had. Overall terrible place'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Well. This was probably the best Karnataka style sambar I had until now. Mind blown. Tea was superb. the front office man was good and I very much liked the food. I'm no foodie and I don't click photos but I can vouch that it is good should eat."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I had come here for lunch. South Indian meal was great. Buttermilk was amazing. Must try coffee here. They have evening snacks as well. Pocket friendly. Worth for the money and the quantity.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Wanna take a small break during work? This is best place for dosa,idli and filter coffee... tried rava dosa... quality is gud. Cashier is friendly and cool guy'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good and reasonable price restaurant which is opened newly in the locality( Brigade Metropolis). loved the food and the service. would suggest and visit again!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Authentic South Indian snacks and dosa items. Loved the food and the quick service at a very reasonable price. The service was exemplary with very detailed attention to the most simple of items. The best part? There's a touch of home in any and every dish that you order. The phrase "Home Sweet Home" has never been truer! Would visit again!! Must tries would be the Rava Masala dosa and Mangalore bonda.'), ('Rated 4.5', "RATED
  Usually don't review or rate on Zomato since the food and the friendly staff made me write this, It so happened I Was on work @ Brigade Metropolis and unusually landed in this small restaurant for a clean south Indian food! Love the DOSA and the butter milk absolutely! Good luck team The South."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Great, authentic food at reasonable prices. Easily the best food available in and around Brigade Metropolis. Everything on their menu from dosas, to idli and vadas to buttermilk is great.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The place is recently opened. We tried the items, Mangalore bonda, onion dosa and mix veg Uthappa. The onion dosa was hard and became like chewy rotti in few minutes. Uthappa was good and Mangalore bonda was reasonable. Overall, an okay place for a quick bite at reasonable prices.')]

column11: Potato Fries, Chicken Curry
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This place serves best grill chicken you can ever have.
The price is pocket friendly and dishes are taste friendly.
The burger wasn't that good.

I had potato wedges, french fries, crispy chicken, grilled chicken and burger.

Grill chicken was cooked way too nicely. Potato wedges and fries were served with Peri Peri as well nice sauce.

Ambience isn't appealing but who cares when you have amazing food for you."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  We ordered from this outlet for home delivery so can't really comment on the service and ambience of this outlet. The menu was having many fried Chicken options and also some rice combo options which make it bit different from other fried Chicken outlets in the town.

We ordered their spicy fried Chicken for two people and it was warm by the time it reached us.

  All the dishes at this place have a great presentation. We tried their pizza, pasta and tiramisu.
Tiramisu is a must try here...
They serve free baguette and ingredients to make brushetta..just follow the steps and try it out. Its quite refreshing and light to have...!!!!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  There is little to write when a place secures full rating. Yet.
Staff is courteous, service is quick given that food is served hot n fresh. Food tastes excellent across all options. Wine listing is long, will take long to be fully explored, probably one of the few places to offer a nice curated menu (barring restaurants in hotels).
If anything to nitpick, since itÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x99s not a pizza joint and intends a fine dine experience, the management could possibly put a small placard on table asking guests to maintain noise levels or decorum, esp when with children.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This is one of the restaurants which I can go blindly any day for good food/healthy food/good ambiance. I have been here few times and had delightful experience each and every time.   Good food and the best Blueberry cheesecake ever! Service is fine. And it isn't too costly either.

  Great place to be. Nice ambience, great food and too good service. Everything we had from starter to main course and pizza and dessert were good. Great experience.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Nice little place but doesn't live up to its ratings on Zomato.
Coming straight to the food, mushroom soup was easily one of the best served in the vicinity. The vegetable soup was quite routine.
Ceasar salad was a bit bland though the chicken was really well cooked. Cristiano pesto chicken was really a let down choice.
The margarita pizza was really good but the lasanga chicken again disappointing. The evening ended on good note with the spaghetti agleo oleo which great.

Really a mixed experience overall."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Excellent option when visiting The Ascendas Park Square Mall.   Chianti Whitefield is not as cosy as many of the other branches. But the generous helpings make up for it.
The waiters here are trained to push the pricey dishes on the menu and they try really hard. If you can ignore that and choose the nice stuff, it really works well. The duck ravioli was heavenly, the pork ribs sumptuous and the fresh carpaccio crunchy with walnuts. The Carbonara was very ordinary. Overall, a decent affair.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Chianti is incapable of disappointing anyone any day!

  Very nice place for desert. I am a big fan of kulfi falooda here. Very refreshing proper flavours. We have tried couple of things here.   Such a delightful place to order from. The desserts are beverages are an absolute steal for the cost. This is a prime example of how they make use of cost effective ingredients in a clever and quirky way. Way to go!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Must go place for lassi, ice-creams and French fries.

Not so good ambience. Sometimes some dishes are unavailable due to lack of water.
Overall, tasty food.')]

column14: [('Rated 1.0', 'RATED\n  This place is not at all good. We had ordered gobi Manchurian in which we got chicken piece. Veg Hyderabadi gravy tastes like vegetables added in green chutney.   ethnic hyderabadi biryani & professional service. I have ordered item for home delivery & received on time with 10 percent off. Really awesome.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  It is Indian and Chinese style small restaurant. Taste of the food is very good . 
I have ordered veg Biryani and baby corn Manchurian . Veg Biryani is too yummy and complimentary sweet along with biryani is just amazing.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  First time I have tried in this place. This biryani comes with bone and with bone with fried onion and perfectly spiced masala.. The Biryani was fresh and the taste was the best i have had in bangalore.  None of the ingredients were overpowering each other, it was perfectly balanced in terms of spice, oil, aroma, amount of masala, tenderness , rice was perfectly cooked.
I am giving 5 because they served a complete meal with Raitha and complementary sweet along with delight Biryani.

Thank you:)'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I thought it is famous for Biryani only but even they prepare best Chinese Fried Rice in the field. Prices also reasonable compared to other places. And they give a complementary sweet at the end so its worth visiting again..'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Taste of Biryani is very good with quality basmati rice...
And that complementary Sweet(Kheer) after having food is a real treat. You should definitely taste this once..'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

column11: Chicken Shashlik, Pasta, Veg Sizzler
column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Have been here 3-4times. This is my food option when we are bored with office canteen. I always take sizzlers here. Taste is good however there is no consistency in taste. At times its good, at times because of the rush the taste is very average.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Words are not enough to describe the taste of the soup I had here.
Cream of tomato- made up with riped tomatoes, rich cream and sprinkled cheese. It tasted just the same as the soup made at home. It came with a few bread crumbs on top giving it a super look.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I have tried Veg Penne Pasta from Hottey Smokey restaurants, overall experience is good. Pasta is tasty and delicious, provided with good packaging.Pasta contain good amount of broccoli and various other vegetables.

My Reviews :
Taste :4/5
Quantity :5/5
Quality :4/5
Satisfaction :4/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  last sunday order here chicken pasta and chciken burger, which was really good, price was reasonable, food was gr8, specially i like that pasta in white sauce, again i am going to order.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I had an emergency in office so I rushed to office on 2nd October. After the completion of work it was time to savour something good.

This place is in food court and easy to find as many people were carrying sizzling hot plates and having as well. Which tempted me to try out this place.

I and my friend asked for chicken satellite and chicken shashilk. I felt Chicken satellite portion was less as I have tried this at different places. The teast was average. They just add cheese and white sauce on chicken. Beans served were not fresh. Chicken shashilk was ok. since rice was accompanied with sizzler it felt more in quantity. French fries were cold and bit over fried.

Nothing special about the place.This place will hit taste buds only if you have not had good sizzler in past. This place is one time try.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Sizzling Sizzlers !! Been here few times and tried their variety of Sizzlers. They are smoking hot. And quantity they provide is decent. The pepper version of any sizzler is too strong peppery flavour. It takes long time to cool these Sizzlers and we end up eating it hot.

Cost is little on higher side and the cabbage is too much below.
Service takes little longer than you expect.')]

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This restaurant specially provide Chinese food. Had ordered chicken noodles and veg spring roll. Price is affordable and taste worth it.

Service staff behavior was very good and quick.

Will recommended others too.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I ordered Mix Non Veg Garlic Noodles and Veg Spring Roll. It was worth it. I loved the food and the price was very much affordable here. Do try it.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Have been here couple of times. Both the times i had chicken sizzler; schezwan and manchurian respectively. The taste is good however the sizzlers lack basic ingredients like tossed veggies & french fries. Also the sauce is very less and hence becomes very dry while eating.

Added a photo of fujian chicken combo. You get rice or noddles, 4 momos, gravy and kimchi salad in this combo. I tried this combo couple of times, during lunch and dinner. There was a huge difference in the taste during both times. For lunch the chicken was all fresh but very much opposite when i took the meal for dinner.'), ('Rated 4.5', 'RATED
  Ordered in for some vegetarian food and loved the taste. Excellent Chinese food. So far, the best chinese food in Whitefield(Bangalore).Will definitely recommend.

Only problem was that quantity was less for 2 people.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Tried their chicken noodles.

Quantity and quality both are good.

Nice behavior from the staff & servive is fast.

Will recommend for others too.

Thank You'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The restaurant provides decent Chinese food. We ordered Egg , chicken and mixed fried rice. Though everything tasted similar, food was good enough with good amount of quantity that could serve 2 per bowl. It will be crowded most of the time,hence delay in serving the order. However felt there's nothing extra ordinary :)"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Have had the food here couple of times, the sizzler here is ok and Manchurian is nice. Fried rice is too bland.

This time i tired Thai green curry with steam rice.
Well- won't ever order this here again. When I got the order first thing what surprised me was the curry colour. It was looking like palak curry! Yes I know I'm comparing Thai cuisine to Indian but that's what it looked like. I felt they had used some kind of colour mostly.
Now coming to taste it was not good!!! Don't expect authentic Thai curry taste.

Service other wise is okish.")]

  Soak some sunshine with a wide spread of lipsmacking menu by pool-side curated by chef Aniket. Yesterday I enjoyed my Sunday brunch followed by a cake-mixing event there. Live music to sooth your soul around the pool with a breezy air. The place is perfect for Family too.you can relax in the pool with a glass of sparkling wine While enjoying some delicious seafood preparations from the live counter. They also have Live Pasta counters , Pancakes , salads and Indian traditional Delicacies that you can't miss them at all. The desserts table was so colorful and every piece of that was worthy to try. Loved my experience and would surely like to recommend.
Food - 5/5
Ambience- 5/5"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  So we happened to choose this place so as to try out a different option which is closer to the office for our team dinner.

Well when we arrived here we were taken back, we were not expecting this big of a hotel inside the tech park which had a good Ambience closer to the office which we never noticed as this is a bit inside.
Food wise they have a nice spread and they have South Indian delicacies as well.
They should improvise on the taste as well as couple of items were bit bland. But overall the food was fine.
It has a cozy and calm atmosphere where you can sit and relax and enjoy your food and drinks.
Do note this is not a party place but a proper corporate restaurant, so the crowd is well behaved and polite.
The staff here were also very polite and helpful.
Well recommended for corporate gatherings and for family gathering where you want to have a calm atmosphere.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  We had been here for lunch on Sunday and had a 1+1 offer on main dishes of dine out. It came up to 1200 for 4 of us. It was great fresh food for the price we paid. Really nice place! The staff is brilliant and Mahi at the restaurant took good care of us! Thanks!')]

  All marks for the Ambiance. A superb outdoor setup to back in the sun or shade sipping beer and chicken wings.   Rainy day and a best place to catch-up with friends and family with the beautiful weather of Bangalore. With the European touch and a street feel they have done it very niche way and it takes you to a different place all-together.

The Food was also very delicious- we tried Nachos, pasta and Pizza, Love Pizza the most.
Do visit if you are in and around whitefield.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Personal favourite place to go to grab a beer in Whitefield. Huge space with multiple seating options which you can decide based on the purpose of your visit. Very chilled out setting which will make you unwind here for hours.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good place for weekend hangout. I went with my friend we both had a great time here... What else you need? Price wise I would give it average, ambience is good, musical vibes from those old progressive house was so relaxing. I will visit this place again...'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Great place!

There are a couple of restaurants and boutique stores here. They have quite a large seating area and can accommodate many people. The parking lot here is huge too. They have outdoor seating as well as indoor seating, people prefer outdoors because it is more appealing. The ambience here is great indeed.

We tried a pasta and a thin crust pizza. The pasta was ordered a bit spicy and it was fiery indeed. Pizza was good too, thin and yummy.

They have their own brewery, and a good selection of beers. They should experiment and come up with more flavours though. The service here is good, though it might take time to get to your table if there is a crowd, which is usually the case on weekends.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  For people living or visiting Whitefield, this is one place where you can enjoy the brilliant Bangalore weather, get a taste of the Whitefield suburb's vibe while you enjoy your pint and company.

Beer, Food, Ambiance: high quality

Tip: definitely sample your beer before ordering

Cheers"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  An open resto bar that gives you a good ambience and palette. The brewery Is good and the platters were loaded. A little not budget friendly but definitely worth the taste'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Well, Amazing place with amazing ambiance and this made the food more amazing ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â°ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x98ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x8a
Loved the pork steeks, wheat beer, non veg platter and few more where in I don really remember those names now..It did good for a bunch of people.
And yes, A very good looking and photogenic place.
Must visit !'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I have visited this place a lot of times. It is a great place to hang out with friends or go for a date. The food here is great and the onion rings are a must try and the nachos are also great the stout and wheat beer is very good. The ambiance of this place is extraordinary as soon as you enter this place you feel you have entered someplace in Europe. Its a must try if you like good ambiance and beer.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The place is worth visiting with friends, ambience is good and it's pet friendly too..Food was quiet okayish though. It was my first visit and hence I asked for suggestions from the staff with regards to their speciality but they couldn't suggest much which is a little strange for me. So finally I ordered what I felt like and unfortunately I didn't enjoy it much. So I guess that could be worked upon. Rest the service was quick and staff was polite..Overall a decent experience but it could have been better."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  One of the popular and finest Brew Pubs of Bangalore with a European set-up. The ambience here calls for some chilling with your gang of friends over few draught beers and nibbles.
We sampled few craft beers and narrowed to the lager flavoured with basil and pepper. Was quite refreshing and flavoursome!
They also have some variety of cocktails on their menu.
Food is okayish but on the expensive side.

Recommended!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Went there on a Saturday night! Was surprised to see that the place wasn't even half full! The location could be an issue for that

We had the Greek pizza and Cheesy stuffed mushrooms! The food was good!"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

Service is great 4/5
Food 4/5
Loved the malai mushrooms and the Mediterranean veg pizza.
Oktoberfest didn't have much to offer though! Limited selection of beers... Do check before you visit."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  They have a variety of in house brews. Tried the ale- nothing really special about it. The taste was pretty fruity- decent flavour.
Food is good too. Tried the chicken- well made.
A little bit expensive and staffing is something they really need to improve.
The location isnt that accessable too.
Overall average experience.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Visited on a rainy evening. My bad luck! No open air table. But the ambiance was beautiful for evening hang out. Brewed beer is awesome.
Food taste was fine and the cost was on the higher side. Overall this place is good for evening chill and beer.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The place is amazing with a good ambience. A visit must be made to this place in the afternoon time and at rhe night time as well, both have a different feel of the place. The food and the beers of this microbrewery are superb. Just one issue I faced becauae of which reduced the rating is that the place is too big and sometimes the staff is not easy to call out to.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Location : It is in the lane behind forum value mall. Not on the main road but easily locatable.

Ambience : Nice open ambience. The street has a couple of mor restaurants so you can choose as per the cuisine and ambience you like.

Food : We ordered wheat beer and spicy chicken pizza.
Liked the beer and pizza was nice and crisp.
Also tried the ale but liked the wheat beer better.

Visit again? : May be.')]

I did not understand taste but my wife and others they loved it. May be something wrong with my taste buds. My wife liked it so I can not say No lol.
You can try though.
Sitting arrangements are good. I will prefer 1st floor. They have 2 section one with AC and one with central cooler. We chose central cooler as we were with 4 months old baby.

Now ratings

Will visit gain'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing place and very yummy and healthy food
Alternative to the routine the food fresh and tasty and just dressing kicks all of it completely dish
And please try Mr karan saud cocktail he suggested best drink'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Super ambience at Seegehalli.. the staff is very courteous. Good food and live music on a Sunday night dinner, will visit again to try other dishes.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Good location and ambience. Food was good, except for the dessert. Fish n chips were good. The Kundapur Chicken was spicy- chilli lovers will like this one.

Bechamel sauce can be a hit or miss but they kind of got it right. To be honest, I did send it back because salt was a bit less. They fixed the dish and it came out right.

The cheese cake was nothing great to be written about. It was too 'gelatinous'. A cheese cake usually melts in your mouth but over here it just lay there like jelly, waiting to be chewed. Something for the chef to think about.

Overall looks like a great place with of food options."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  They have opened an outlet in Whitefield recently. The interior is really good. We ordered Panko crumpled fry chicken (Average) and Chicken Stroganoff (which was amazing). Food took a bit time to arrive and the service was average. But would definitely visit again to try other dishes.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Brilliant food and service shows up at Seegehalli! We ordered dinner, and to our pleasant surprise every dish was equally sumptuous. The only disappointment was portion size that seemed disproportionate to price. But again special thanks to Diptikant, restaurant manager, who turned this feedback to action and shipped us additional portions instantly! Super impressed! Keep up the good work OFTR!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  ItÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x99s a nice place.. the staff is very courteous and humble. The mock tails recommended by them were really good. The veg sizzler we ordered was disappointing. The white sauce spaghetti was tasty. They can definitely improve their mains.')]

  Incredible place! Very large seating area. Amazing service, and food was absolutely fantastic. Each and every dish ordered was delicious. Good dancing space. DJ was amazing!'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  We went for Sunday brunch. The variety in the buffet menu was less, also, the menu was more like a lunch buffet than a brunch. Starters included crispy corn, veg kabab, seekh kabab, chicken tikka, chicken wings, chilly chicken, etc. There was only one live counter for pasta and eggs. The main course was pretty much the usual, nothing noteworthy. Variety in desserts was okay. But none of the desserts were exceptional.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  One of the best brewery in whitefield. The staff is really hospitable. Amanda the manager made sure we have the best experience mixing the brew and the food that goes along woth it. I strongly recommend spending an evening at the pallet and falling in love with the pine German wheat.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We had been here on a Thursday and I was surprised to find it packed at around 7 in evening. They have happy hours till 7. Their starters are descent to good in taste and they serve platters only after 6.
I also like the ambience made with wooden planks placed in a pattern.
Their service was quite bad. They came to our table with multiple wrong orders.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Great place
1. HUUGEE.
2. Great ambience
3. Good food.
4. Awesome service
5. Kid friendly. A magician came and entertained the kids and adults alike'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Never can go wrong with pallet, good food nice service , also good beer!..also very good ambiance..dance floor is open for everyone after 10p.m

Food :5/5
Drink : 4/5
Price : 4/5'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The service was quite bad. Food was average and didnÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x99t like it much as you expect better from a 4.5 rated one.

Seems like they accommodate more people than they can manage with the staff strength.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had a great experience with big group of friends. Enjoyed bollywood night music and the Dhol entry. Awesome dance floor and enjoyed the time spend here.
I would recommend this place for hanging out with group of friends to party.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Located in Whitefield, this is one of the big breweries of Bangalore. This place has a very vibrant Ambiance and great infrastructure. I personally liked the way how wood is made use of here. I was here for a quick visit and tried out all samplers before I decided to order just one out of all the available ones.

I ordered a pizza which was pretty good in taste but the size was very small! Not worth the price definitely. The beer wasn't upto the mark as well. I request the management to fine tune the taste of beers here."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Had been to this place when had my visit to Banglore and one must say that this place is super cool. From the food to the drinks and the best part of this place is that it has an Amazing dance floor. A must visit if you plan a trip to Banglore and you love to dance.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  The mushroom starters served here has no competition whatsoever. The pizzas are good too. The ambience on a weekday n on a weekend is literally poles apart but both enjoyable. The servers are fun too. Being in whitefield this is a go to place for everyone working nearby ! The music is very loud so if youre looking for a quiet meal i wouldn't recommend this, its very lively !"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Awesome ambience. Good food and drinks we were in Saturday night we enjoyed with dhol and the dj..And the service by Mr.Badal such a nice guys...i like this place a lot we ll come soon'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing place with some mouthwatering food and beers. Happy hours are the best time to visit this place.

I ordered Guava Mary, Cheese corn spinach dumplings, Chilly Basil cottage cheese.

  Pallet is a really good fine dining brew pub in Whitefield. The decor is easily a 5/5. Staff is courteous and I would give them 4/5. The food is extremely tasty and would give a 4.5/5 for taste. Portions would be 3.5/5 and value for money would be 3.5/5.

We ordered Veg Nachos, Dahi Kebab and Hyderabadi Talawa Gosth. I put down my head down and focused on the Gosth so had to ask my wife for opinions on the nachos and Dahi Kebab. The Gosth was excellent, awesome flavours and the meat was really tender, must try!. The Nachos was good and so was the Dahi Kebab. Personally I liked the Dahi Kebab more than the nachos.

They have 2+2 on drinks for Zomato gold members and I had a Hot Toddy and Mahogany Triple Wheat craft beer. Loved the Hot Toddy and the beer was also really good.

The Lava Cake truly was the icing on the cake. Will definitely come back to try out more dishes here.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Nice ambiance,, they have used the packing pallets everywhere. We had been there on a friday afternoon. Even though its a buffet, they serve the starters at the table. We had to wait for a long time for a particular starter and when it arrived we were already having the main course. So basically they have to improve a lot on their service. Food is good, specially the thai prawn curry. We didn't try their brews. Want to visit once again and hoping the service would be better"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Pallet is a really good fine dining brew pub in Whitefield. The decor is easily a 5/5. Staff is courteous and I would give them 4/5. The food is extremely tasty and would give a 4.5/5 for taste. Portions would be 3.5/5 and value for money would be 3.5/5.

We ordered Veg Nachos, Dahi Kebab and Hyderabadi Talawa Gosth. I put down my head down and focused on the Gosth so had to ask my wife for opinions on the nachos and Dahi Kebab. The Gosth was excellent, awesome flavours and the meat was really tender, must try!. The Nachos was good and so was the Dahi Kebab. Personally I liked the Dahi Kebab more than the nachos.

They have 2+2 on drinks for Zomato gold members and I had a Hot Toddy and Mahogany Triple Wheat craft beer. Loved the Hot Toddy and the beer was also really good.

The Lava Cake truly was the icing on the cake. Will definitely come back to try out more dishes here.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Nice ambiance,, they have used the packing pallets everywhere. We had been there on a friday afternoon. Even though its a buffet, they serve the starters at the table. We had to wait for a long time for a particular starter and when it arrived we were already having the main course. So basically they have to improve a lot on their service. Food is good, specially the thai prawn curry. We didn't try their brews. Want to visit once again and hoping the service would be better"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

column11: Keema Pav, Cocktails, Craft Beer, Pork Chops, Mocktails, Hefeweizen, Nachos
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  A review for Windmills has been a long overdue for me. For me Windmills is not just any joint but one where I am sure if I visit I'll feel relaxed and at ease. That's how it has been for a few years now. Good food, great service, superb ambience and if you happen to have good company, there is no place better. I have spent 3-4hrs at a stretch with friends and family at this place. The pictures that you see are from 2 different visits, alias I couldn't find the rest. I have generally visited this place on Saturdays after a week of hard work, to prep for the next one to come. To many more visits, keep rocking"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing ambience! The music .. jazz! Everything gives the place a touch of calmness much needed to break the humdrum of the hustling cityy!
Food was great! drinks were one of their kind ! Staff super friendly!
Worth a visit!   I have been here multiple times and in fact yesterday I was there for dinner with my friends.
It's a very sophisticated restaurant and the Ale is excellent. They probably make the best fresh beer in town. The food is also very good. But the restaurant is a bit congested as they don't have enough space. You'll surely like the beer and the food here but remember that it's an expensive place for dining. But it's worth the money."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Visited Windmills Craftworks with a friend yesterday... The place is absolutely awesome. The location and music makes for a fabulous ambience.. Their strout beer is famous. Had their chicken ceasar salad which was extremely delicious and one of the best I've had. Their desserts are delicious too and strongly recommended. Its a must visit for a perfect evening. I would definitely visit again whenever I am in the city next."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Lived up to their reputation, all the dishes I ordered were delicious. Tried chicken Ceaser salad, chicken sliders, broccoli tikki for starters and it was yum,except chilli surprise in broccoli tikki. Pine ginger and red sea mocktails were nice as well. Kheema mattar pao was surprise indian touch and it was yum and must try. Finally Green apple.crum for dessert stood out both in presentation and taste.

Food 4/5
Ambience 4/5

Tablets for ordering were pretty slow and non responsive ( not user friendly).'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Be the service or beverage, all in all landmark property
. Well educated and trained staff with good knowledge of what was actually served on the table.'), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  So, Friday night we decide to grab a few drinks and we were in Whitefield. I have heard so much about windmills craftworks and I thought it was the perfect time to try it out.
They were having a performance that night and they said we could have a table till 8, reached around 6:45. We decided to stay on, placed an order in another 10 minutes.
At 7:30, when we asked the waiters regarding the order, they said that the order was not placed. The app they use is terrible and the waiters didn't care to check. And they did not even have the courtesy of letting us know ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â°ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x98ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80 just a few tables were full. We had to leave and then we headed to oota.
I'm definitely not going back!"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Visited this place on a weekday. Place is really nice with very good options of food with buffet. Taste of food was not that good. Not willing to visit again.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  One of the finest dining place in Bangalore, innovative drinks , super amazing food and staff is also courteous.. only issue is seating availability...'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  This place is so beautiful, the ambience is lovely and the music is absolutely the best. Everything seems better with good music in the background.
It's really difficult to get a table here but we went on a weekday afternoon and got it easily.
The beer is great, the food was good too.
Everything was perfect, but I feel there can be more food options."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Located a bit inside white field, this microbrewery is one of kind. I recently went to have lunch with couple of my friends and my experience was good. Usually this place is crowded and getting a outside sitting is almost impossible (Trust me the view is awesome :)). Each and every table is assigned to a guide and orders can be placed on the tab. We had grilled broccoli kebabs and Falafel for lunch which was pretty good. We all had hefeweizen beer which was really fantastic. Would love to come back again.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Food - 3.75/5
Drinks - 4.5/5
Ambience - 4.25/5
Service - 3.5/5
Value for money - 3/5

A little disappointing for all the hype created around this place. The food was decent, not extraordinary. The drinks were really good - definitely try their mango beer. The ambience is good, but was a little too crowded for my liking. The staff were a bit slow, not in serving food but the service altogether was a bit slow and hotchpotchy but it might be because of the crowd. All in all a decent experience, but not a five star experience.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A really sophisticated place to enjoy a dinner date with loved one, enjoy quality time or have fun with friends(Not tooo Loud Talks though :-P). 

Went with two of my friends and had great time with them!

We Ordered : Craft Beers, Paneer Tikka, LIIT, Nachos, Lasagne.
The food was amazing to have. Craft Beers have good taste, with detailed description on the menu, it is easy to decide!!

Ambience : The place is well spacious and decorated! Lighting and mood gets well into the ambience!
Service : Staff is very co-operative and attentive.

Sugggestions : Add Menu to the Zomato!

Must visit place on a fine dine with family and friends!!! Enjoyed the Time!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The place offers both open air and AC seating. And it's a real tease as both the options are amazing. The inside seating is super classy and chic. Outside one has it's classic charm. We opted for outside seating - a bit of a bummer here as despite pre-reservation, they did not keep a table for us outside. But they did accommodate us somehow. Later when there was place, we had to ask to be shifted. A bit more promptness in service can go the extra mile here. 

Now coming to more awesomeness. The cutlery and china they use is as classy and unique as the place. We missed live music but I am told the place rocks some really nice one. 

The beer sampler presentation was amazing. Their wheat beer is amazing; rest, just about ok. 

Must go."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Love the general buzz of this place... Sophisticated without screaming pretentiousness.
The food, looks brilliant and the taste just as brilliant. Those cocktails were unique and deeelicious. Not a beer person, but I hear the brews here are one of the best as well.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  This is such a boring place I have ever been on a new year eve. Giving 2 rating only because of ambience. Loved the Ambience pretty cool. It's awesome with perfect lighting, decors and sitting arrangements. But they were playing all boring melody songs. It completely ruined our evening.

  Though the entire building is owned by Windmill, there are 3 restaurants on floors 6,7,8 - namely Windmills Craftworks, Oota and Terrace. The ambience of Oota is very nice and different.

Windmills on floor 6 is elegant and has classy music. But frankly their staff's attitude is a bit disturbing. I would surely recommend their Gralic bread but not their Honey Chilly Potato. They are usually heavily booked so do reserve a seat before you walk in. Overall I think that this restaurant is over rated."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  Been to WC recently, situated bang on in middle of EPIP hustle bustle. Wallet parking available. Been to terrace that's on 8th floor. It has few tables covered and rest of table in open, with canopy to protect from sunlight and rain. Lighting is bit on a dim side. It has live chat counter, bar, buffet spread. Starters are served on table, but plates meant for starters is very small, they should change them for sure. Mutton fry didn't had Mutton flavor, prawns were way too small, only thing which i liked was Paneer and fish tikka. Coming to chat counter, it has chat along pani poori, jalebi, chole kulcha. Amritsari kulcha with chole i liked most. In buffet spread lots of variety, Mutton paya soup was awesome, lots of salads. Even main course had lots of option for veg and non veg. In dessert counter no ice-cream but other options in ample amount. Friendly staff, that's why going with 3 rating. In this price you will definitely find better food and ambience for sure."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
