column14:
[('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  HQ is located at ground floor of Inorbit Mall, WF. The decor is premium and sophisticated. We were denied sofa seats on pretext that those were already reserved. Ironically I also had reservation but I guess they had their reasons. We had two Gold memberships. I ordered Pork Belly and kept waiting for 50 mins. After intimating that my order is late, I was told that the dish was not available and they were sorry about it. I reordered another dish which took another 15 or 20 mins. Mac and Cheese ball were nice, the presentation even better (pics attached). Staff was friendly and prompt. The music was a little too loud for my liking specially for the kind of vibe the restaurant has. Nachos were below par, pizza at par. The catch is that the restaurant applies 18 percent tax. We were told it is because it comes under Mariott building or something like that. Still didn't get the point. Overall a OKish experience."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Very good ambience ,
And food taste is too good..
Nachos was too good ..
Pizza were thin crust so it was very uncomfortable to eat the way they served ..taste was good though....
Worth the money ...good place to hangout out on weekends'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  First visit to HQ and it was a totally bad choice. Service was slow! Me and my friends visited the place to have beer and after ordering Budweiser brew, what we got was a mixed taste of beer and water. When checked with the manager he says it is like that itself. Tasted beer a billion times and this was the worst of all! This is my last visit and would never visit the place again!

Tip: Make sure to take care of the customers who visit ur place rather than having a chit chat. Literally I had to get up off my spot and call them to issue the bill!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Explored this swanky new place in Whitefield just a few miles from our office. It is located on top of the Inorbit Mall and the place is a beauty. It has a superb ambience and we all loved it. There is indoor as well as outdoor seating. The food is pretty good and so is the service. They serve some good beers on tap(Not brewed by them though) and is a perfect hangout for friends and colleagues. We ordered Whiskey sours, Geist Witty Wit and some quick bites. They were good except for the fact that the Whiskey sour didn't quite taste like a whiskey sour. I didn't get a chance to taste their other cocktails but will visit them again to get a taste of them. Overall a very decent place for hanging out."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  What a beautiful ambience. It is so green and a quiet place. Best for dates and quiet dinners. We didn't like the food much but the drinks are pretty good. Mostly the ambience stole my heart."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Wonderful ambience. Wonderful food and service. I would have preferred that the air-conditioning was better as we were feeling hot but as Food and ambience was good we chose to focus on that. We ordered Thai Basil Chicken, HQ - A lot Pizza, Thai Red curry with rice and every dish was unique to the restaurant and we liked it.   Food: 3/5

Ambience: 5/5
Location:5/5

Cleanliness: 5/5

Far off from the city but situated in a peaceful place.

Food we ordered was served well.

French fries are the best and its worth every penny.

The myo is very tasty there.

Naga chicken is not very good so recommend you some other dishes.

Fish is ok but had different taste and flavours.

Mocktail is very good there.

The ambience is stunning and lively.

We also got a complementary pizza as it was new year eve.

We like the place and ambience with drink.

Food is bearable except for french fries.

The complementary pizza had a very bad taste.

Food needs improvement in the place but ambience takes it all over.

They do not have zomato gold.

One time go place for food and drink.

For any future questions drop in : thekhanalovers@gmail.com

One time go place for food and drink.

  I went with a friend of mine last week. A great rooftop ambience i must say. As soon as we entered we asked for a place for two and were assisted to the seats. I noticed that the the cushion was dirty, someone had stepped on it. Didn't expected that.
Coming to food... The menu is minimum but still the food was good. We ordered beer at first, we asked if Kingfisher strong beer was available. The guy said yes and served us with Kingfisher Ultra and said it is a strong beer, which clearly wasn't. Anyone can clearly read the alcohol %age and tell which is a strong beer. We took whiskey later.
The food took around 20min to serve. We had pork bellies, chicken wing and beef too. The beef was kinda overcooked.
The music was loud and our seats were just next to it. But it was okay-ish.
Price was kinda mid-expensive.

Based on my experience,

column14:
[('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Went with Team on Thursday Evening to the place. My experience was not great as Beer was warm as they did not had cold one available. Food was not great (Nachos, Pizza and Peanuts were average) , Ambiance was Just OK. Overall staff was supportive, but place need better service. 

May be its will be able to mint money due to its nearness to Prestige Shantiniketan, but overall Lousy place'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I went for an afternoon lunch... limited buffet option but again charges are 499..so pretty ok...they had only 2 beer options though menu talks a lot...
Its a terrace restaurant so should be more fun during evening..
Food was ordinary.. nothing too great...'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Great place for rooftop beer lovers with nice music.
Loved the prawn tempura, pasta and noodles. We also had ordered a non-veg platter which had tandoori items, it was good. The bubble bath cocktail was nice. In short, food and drinks are just bang on. Would definitely love to visit again.
Waiters are polite but not responsive, making the service little slow.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Yet another pub with a view? Yes, maybe but who minds that? Rooftop bar with a nice enough food menu, decent crowd, nice music and a view of the Sheraton hotel and Forum Shantiniketan to boot. Plus the Gold encourages you to drink ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x98em up!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  We visited on Bollywood night and utilized our zomato gold 2+2 drinks. Staff was very kind. We ordered veg soup which was pathetic n too sour. Though, we did not enjoy bollywood night much as DJ was playing all the songs till it ends. Their quantity was very less. Only peanut masala I liked. Their drinks were good n high alcohol content.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Visited this place last evening with a bunch of friends. Since it was a weekday there was hardly anyone. It has a simple but pleasant ambience. Dance floor is very small. It can hardly accommodate 10 people. They need to hire another DJ. Music sucked. We ordered veg and non veg platter, fries, rotis, dal makhani and couple of veg and non veg dishes to go with rotis. Food was just okay. Cocktails were fine and we could utilise zomato gold membership well. Service was quick. Staff is very friendly and helpful. Ashok took good care of us.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Such a cool place just opposite to prestige Shantiniketan IT park. Very lively place and you can definitely enjoy your weekend over here. Food is also nice. Prawn was really yummy. Nice ambience and they have rooftop sitting as well. Overall such an amazing experience.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Great Friday night with delicious food and amazing music .. the drinks are great with great outdoor seating .. a must got after office and weekend parties with friends .. the DJ also plays Bollywood music which is very rare in Bangalore .. chicken Daredevil is a must try here with some other amazing starters !'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This place is just opp to Grand Sheraton ..I went there with my friends the place is amazing in one building they have owned three floor 1st floor they are serving buffet in lunch.The 2nd floor is Al Fresco and you can say Heart of the Restaurant and top floor for cocktail parties and you can enjoy the beautiful view from there in breezy air.

We start our Dinner with ther Refreshing Beverage which was prepared by Bartender Ajay ..

Lets talk about FOOD...
The Executive Chef #Diwas came him self in our table to suggest there best dishes .we tried there home made nachos spicy fries tandoori chicken and Harisha chicken which was cumin flavor each and every dishes was very delicious.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A nice new place in Whitefield.. best is the open sit out. All the cocktails are great.. but somehow we indulged ourselves in multiple Kalhua shots which was incredible.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Good to see such place in Whitefield area and that too close to office. Really impressed with the ambience. Roof top is what I liked the most. Coming to food we ordered naga's chicken, gnocchi, stuffed chicken breast, prawns rissoto and AL' arrabiata non veg pasta. Food was good and tasty but gnocchi and stuffed chicken breast needs more improvement.

Service was good and satisfied with it. Will surely visit again."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  We wanted to try this new place in Whitefield and so happened to be here on a Saturday late evening. This place is bang opposite Sheraton grand above Cult Fit. There is no valet parking available but easy to park in the alley near the football court. The ambience on the roof top is good and you get a beautiful view of the skyline. They have a double rooftop which was cool. Crowd was minimal as it's a new place but will surely pick up with time. Brewed beers are not available but I was told they were working on it. Until then one will need to manage with the bottled beers. The cocktails and my drinks were good. The choice of food on the menu looked good. And well the food was delicious. The staff was courteous and knowledgeable and the service was quick. There was lovely music playing in the background which we enjoyed. Overall had a great evening."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

Sorry but unfortunately my experience was not good in Socials and same with my friends.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

We ordered the Cesar salad which was fine.

The butter garlic prawns was the best amongst all the dishes we ordered.

The grilled peri peri chicken sizzler missed something. We didnÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x99t see it sizzling.

The kheema pav was a bit on the spicier note. But it was good.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  To start, the ambience and vibe of the place are absolutely spot on, similar to other Social outlets across the country. Seating, however, was not very comfortable, with chairs either being rickety or too straight backed.
We were 2 of us, and we ordered a Mac and Cheese, Momo chaat and butter chicken biryani for food. Mac and cheese was heavenly, momo chaat could have been avoided, and while the butter chicken was decent enough, its flavour was slight different than the one they serve in the Hauz Khas, Delhi outlet. For drinks, we ordered a white wine sangria which was a little too sweet for my liking, and a smoked Jim Beam cocktail that was interesting.
While overall it was a good experience, one thing that could have definitely been better is the service, not only was it too slow, but you had to repeat yourself multiple times.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Probably the smallest Social in terms of area In Bangalore but being in Phoenix market city is a big advantage, close to my home and I love the place for breakfasts options. It delivers to my home and that helps too.

My wife absolutely loves the China box in social, itÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x99s a must try, its our comfort food now.

I have probably tried all the items from the 1st food page of Social, the breakfast options and love Poori Aloo Nashta, HarmeetÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x99s Chic breakfast and Dhingra Punjabi Big tray is awesome too.

Sandwiches are big and loaded served with fries and make them a good option too. Mac and cheese paste is also a regular for me.

In drinks I love their homemade Lemonade, and social toxic LITs are always fun.

I am definitely coming to this place again, very soon.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I was shopping at Phoenix Marketcity with a friend when we stopped by at Whitefield Social to have lunch. It was giving a happy vibe so we chose this place. We were lucky enough to get a table as soon as we walked in despite being a Saturday. 

The service and ambiance were great. The menu had a lot of varieties of food and drinks. We ordered the following dishes:

Crispy sesame honey chili fries - It was crispy and amazing.

Butter chili garlic veg momo - It was one of the best momos I have had in a while. It is mouthwatering, indeed!

Jalapeno mac n cheese with parmesan crust - It was cheesy and delicious.

Ferrero Rocher shake - It was tasty but quantity was less compared to its cost.

Virjin Mojito - It was refreshing.

Would recommend this restaurant to grab some lunch while shopping!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
 
Socials has always been my go to place, everything I visit that part of the city (pheonix mall).
A nice place to hangout and enjoy food over drinks (alcohol & non alcohol - a treat for both preference)
For a place known for its liquor, it has some amazing ice tea and food; my top picks will explain it all.
Service is good and welcoming and ambience has a rustic yet modern feel to it.
Post shopping of your looking to relax and enjoy some good food, one should definitely visit the Whitefield Socials.

Place - Whitefield Social
Ambience - 5/5
Service - 4/5
Price - 850 (for 2 people/without alcohol)
Taste - Palatable
Top picks - Lemon Ice tea, chicken Nachos, Andra Mutton Briyani, China boxes, Southall fish & chips, Achari Basa, Social Kichdi, Chocolate Blood bath.
Final Verdict: 5/5'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  It's a good place for groups. All the items ordered tasted pretty good. Service was good, food took a reasonable amount of time to reach our table, and the price was very reasonable. Ambience was nice. They have Foosball here as well."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This is a nice place in Phoenix market City Mall. The tenderloin sizzler was really good. They do have a lot of space and the service is good.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  after 8 months Today, i just visited social in Phenoix Marketcity, my overall experience was good, i ordered fresh vegetable panino sandwich, toberl shake and chicken momos, all really good especially shake , i really liked it. Ambience is ok , staff is nice . it is value to money'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Unique place with unique way of service

Pros: variety of food and drinks, unique presentation of food and serving style.

Cons: little costly

Visit this place and get amazed with the place, menu and the way they serve you ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â°ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x98ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Wow, this is a great place to enjoy with ur friends and coligues, we went there there a few days ago , enjoying a lot with social vibes , social food, drinks and amazing service. We had fried chicken bucket, biriyani, China box chicken , butter chicken biryani. I recommend most of those this. Thanks u social given us a great evening.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  This is the first social visited among the many in Bangalore. The place is not very big as expected. We were lucky to get a table outside as soon as we walked in inspite of being a Saturday. The menu has a lot of varieties for food and drinks and the presentation is also very impressive. We stuck to drinks and starters and both tasted good .The service was quick , the only draw back is the cleanliness. Would like to visit the other socials and then decide the best oneÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â°ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x98ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x8a'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Been here a number of times as it always manages to give a happy vibe.
The thing that makes this place different is their crockery and their newspaper styled menu.
For drinks they have quite good options in cocktails though I cannot say the same for beers. Their LLIT is strong and LIT as it comes in a measuring cylinder.
Food is average taste wise, good starters and veg China box noodles is atop.
Service can be better.
Indoor and outdoor sitting area is available and to sharpen your skills in foosball they also have a foosball table.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Whitefield social is the first pub to me after coming to bangalore. Place is quite happening. Music was great. Socials are always makes feel good.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Socials never dissapoints!
Have visitye this place a couple of times,and be it the quality of food,taste,service,and LIIT everything is awesome.paneer biryani was great and the croquettes were okay,loved chana jor garam and the fryums.amazing songs played at the end!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Had been here on a Sunday. It was my first visit to whitefield social. Good things 1st. There was no waiting,I hoped on as I reached. Ambience was good not great. Bad things starts now, cleanliness was a issue here as tables were lil sticky. Food ordered was delayed cuz of some reason. On service part it was ok. Food dint taste as good as in kormangala. My over all experience in kormangala was way better than this social. It was a okok visit. Couldnt hold to the expectation.
Had great expectation as kormangala social is one of ma favourite places to go in blore. Whitefield dint live upto that.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Heard so much about this place, had to visit. It lived up to my expectations in terms of ambience and affordability. I had higher expectations from the quality of food. Only liked the sizzlers. Taste is pretty average and for a few dishes, even below average. May visit again only for the sizzlers.'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Nice place. Good ambience mainly due to the activities that happen in front of PVR. Inside and outside seating is available. Food and drink pricing is on par with the market, but was disappointed with the taste. I ordered the cottage cheese and capsicum sizzler, them thick skinned potatoes and a fresh lime soda. Individually, the sizzler was decent. Only complaint was that the quantity of rice was very less. The Paneer was soft and well seasoned, but lacked that kick of flavor. The mushrooms were a outstanding. The other veggies occupied space. Rice was also very mildly seasoned. May be its catered to a blander palette.

Them thick skinned potatoes need to be avoided at all costs. Very bland. No salt, spice or anything nice. Was just a shell with cheese and mush.

The soda was the savior.

Service also needs improvement. Lot of wait time between a waiter checking up on us. Probably wont go again.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Been meaning to go here for a long time Nd finally was able to after attending one of the music concerts at the mall
Wow the energy the whole place has absolutely superb and on. Friday night a mix of fun and craziness which I personally love
Good music food drinks ambience and friends we just had to get up and shake a leg wherever bwe found place
The LIT s as always are superb and
Fish and chips and Mac and cheese yummy
The kebabs too'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Social has always been a go to place in whichever city or area. Rarely rate places this less. But wouldn't recommend this place if in this area.
There are several other options in bars and cafes if you are looking to have a good time here.
Was here on a holiday evening, the entire mall was packed and so was social.
Decided to catch up with a few friends here and after a 30minute wait we got a seat inside. The music was jarring loud, despite repeated requests from multiple people the manager seemed incompetent to reduce the volume and the DJ just didn't seem to care about his audience.

The food was disappointing. Unlike all other social outlets, the taste was different and not what I had in mind. The service was slow, extremely disappointing and not at all social like.
No bottled beer options was available. Only one draught beer option and one bottled beer."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We went on a weekend, but there was not much crowd,still we have got a disappointing service,had to call them for everything. Keeping that aside,food was good,I liked the starters more than main course'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The best thing about this place is its ambience. Food is also good. Chicken kabab and coctails are good. Chicken ghee roast is not that great better to taste that in any good manglorean restaurant. This place is located in Phoenix market city which is one of the happening malls in Bangalore.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice ambience, good food but the service can be better. Even on a weekday afternoon when most tables were empty we had to wait. The cheesy nachos was to good to resist.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

Had a great time sitting outside because usually social has loud music inside!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Am surprised I hadn't posted a review till now. Social has managed to retain it's standards with this outlet, clearly the buzziest in this area. And today we actually did a brunch here which was equally good... from the paranthas to the eggs! Service is a little ad hoc but pleasant. One of the few go-to places... from breakfast to drinks!"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  This outlet doesn't have the vibe of a Social. Being small in size it has very less seating available. But coming on to food and drinks, it stands right where it should be. The LIIT is always the best drink on the Social menu, though I was surprised that they ran out of bottled beers on a Saturday night. I think it should improvise on its decor and service."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This is one of the cafes where it doesn't matter if you drink or not as the food is also awesome. Have visited the place several times and tried Fully loaded nachos, Croquettines, Jalapeno Cheese balls and the tiffin with all the possible combinations of peanuts, chana jor garam etc. and the food will never disappoint you here! Even tried the cold dark coffee and it was amazing. The ambience is also great and gives a real social feel with the typical cutlery and the decor."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The thing I like the most about Social is the serving size of most of the dishes. It is better than most bars I have been to. Their China boxes are a must try.   This outlet doesn't have the vibe of a Social. Being small in size it has very less seating available. But coming on to food and drinks, it stands right where it should be. The LIIT is always the best drink on the Social menu, though I was surprised that they ran out of bottled beers on a Saturday night. I think it should improvise on its decor and service."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  This is one of the cafes where it doesn't matter if you drink or not as the food is also awesome. Have visited the place several times and tried Fully loaded nachos, Croquettines, Jalapeno Cheese balls and the tiffin with all the possible combinations of peanuts, chana jor garam etc. and the food will never disappoint you here! Even tried the cold dark coffee and it was amazing. The ambience is also great and gives a real social feel with the typical cutlery and the decor."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The thing I like the most about Social is the serving size of most of the dishes. It is better than most bars I have been to. Their China boxes are a must try. column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I never knew of this place till I actually went there. Nestled between VR mall and Phoenix, I don't know how I never took notice of this brewery, but it's a very cosy and quaint place with the option of outdoor seating. With the breeze coming through, this is a great place to catch up with friends.
The drinks are better than the food, which was a slight disappointment because if they elevate their food, it will be one of the few places which can boast of great food and drinks.
We ordered the wings which was the best, but I found their vegetarian fare better than the non veg.
However , overall the staff is good, drinks are great and food is ok to get by."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Went in with low expectations at first and the pub was fairly empty at first (around 5 30 PM on a weekend) so I actually felt like walking out immediately. But laziness made me stick around.

The ambience is nice on the outside area, especially the entrance route and the history of Blore. The inside was a little bland. This place has tried to get an anglo-indian (specifically kannadiga) vibe with the name of the beers and dishes

The food was good - the fries starter and the chicken starters we're both good.

The IPAs were both good (Whitefield brew especially) but the wheat beer was a little too sweet for my liking.

Very good value for money - even more so with Zomato Gold."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Plenty of open space is USP of this place and ambiance is pretty good.

Drinks: Limited brewed beer options in stock but Wheat beer was good. Scope of improvement in Margaritas.

Food: Very Good. No fault in any of the dishes that we ordered. We tried - Mushroom Poppers, Baby Corn Mushroom Masala, Chilli Cheese Toast and Infantry Special (spicy but worth a try)

Parking is available within the VR mall.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I loved the ambience and the food here. The menu is more pocket friendly than one would expect from the ambience. The staff is courteous and friendly. The craft beers are pretty good, and the food was really well prepared and presented as well. We ordered the chef's special chicken starter and a chicken burger. Will try the Sunday brunch the next time I'm there"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A really nice place to try. Quiet place with a nice ambiance, which is good when one comes all tired after work on a weekday.
The beers we tried was good too. The mushroom poppers and the burgers were tasty as well. We also tried the desserts - Chocolate sin for two, which was delicious. I would love to visit here again.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I'd been meaning to visit The Whitefield Arms for a while and I made the wise decision to drop in for lunch on a weekday. The place is nice and quiet and with not many people in the restaurant the service was great and with the happy hour the deal on the beers was neat. I absolutely loved the brews we ordered - the Winston and the Lancer. The fish and chips and the Steak we ordered was well cooked and tasty. I'd definitely drop in again, and soon."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  We went with office team today . The ambience is really unique basically the outdoor seating . The food is really tasty and service is really fast n good . Happy hours is great .'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Food is decent, nothing exotic. But then again fish items were above average.

Ambience was good though.
Burger items could have been much better.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

The restaurant offers 2+2 on brewed beer as well.

We visited the place at time of pongal and the outside sitting area was well decorated to give us festive feeling of pongal.

They had live music as well which was great.

Food:4/5
Ambience: 4/5
Cost for 2: 1500rs'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This has to be one of those places that was a pleasant surprise to me. Went in for a brunch on Sunday but ended up ordering A la carte because the brunch menu was just north indian food with a continental starters and the name of the place leads you to believe it is Anglo Indian cuisine but that being said the a la carte menu was lovely. We had the pork belly, the beef roulade which were lip smacking and well made. For mains we ordered pork and mash, the pork chops and the railway Mutton curry which were also good. There were only two beers available and the Whitefield brew is a good choice. Overall a good, fun place to hang out with friends for a Sunday brunch or lunch. Will definitely be coming back but I do hope they rehash their brunch menu!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Went for a casual snacks on a Saturday afternoon. Had The Winston beer, it was average, and onion rings were good, specially the mustard sauce . Ambience is quite good, staff is courteous and fast service.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  We landed up at this place to exploit zomato gold benefit honestly and it turned out to be completely worth it.

Visited this place on late Friday night.It wasn't that crowded.Loved their Cosmopolitan and in house brewed beer.(the citrus flavour one,can't seem to recall the name).

Ambiance is lovely.It has got a an open and close seating area.The closed one is dim lit and really good for a date.

The open space is beautiful too but beware of the mosquitoes ruining your date.

Service was quick.

Would definitely visit again!"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Absolutely loved the place and would visit again. We took the outdoor seats under the shade. The weather was perfect outside to enjoy the cozy place. The starters, mains and the LIITs we ordered were superb. This being a microbrewery, we were initially a bit disappointed as the craft beers got over but everything else made up for it eventually.

We were served by Prakash, he was polite and courteous while tending to our orders and very happy with his service. He also made us a brilliant flaming shot fountain in the end.

Ambience 4.5/5
Food 4.5/5

I have been here two times and the staffs are friendly and nice. Overall i would suggest to go once and try out.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Very different taste in things I tried. The staff is very polite as well. I tried two dishes and one mocktails which were really great in taste. Spaghetti and fries can be tried if you like them.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Went to this place on weekday evening and it has a beautiful ambience .
Great wooden decor and beer quotes .
They have happy hours from 5 to 8pm on some weekdays ... And craft beer they have as well domestic and international too .
We had their jalapenos cheese fondue veg . And my god, it was delicious and mind-blowing. I always wanted to try fondue and it was the best . Set a very high standard of fondue in my head .
Not giving 5 stars coz yes it is a bit over priced . And Zomato gold doesn't stand valid on each menu item. It's quite limited to few items only."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  It was a Monday night I visited this place with couple of my friends ,the moment I enter this place there was no one to well come, I had to find a table by myself even service was so late ,,,man it took more than 20 min to prepare one cocktail are u kidding me,,,food was delicious must improve the quality of service,,,,,,,,,,the ambiance is so cool specially the outdoor seating and also inside the mall u have a smoking zone great man...chalo thank you'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The decor is cool and that of an old irish bar with some modern touch.

Must try

Melon brainfreeze
Irish coffee
Drunken prawns
Jalapeno and corn cheese fritters
The melting pot
Beetroot and goat cheese sliders
Dual chocolate tart
Devilish chocolate brownie

The service was initially quick.Later the waiter got changed and there was confusion.

Watermelon and ginger margarita had little hint of tequila.The melon had diluted the tequila to the extent that i felt it was a melon refresher.I did get a replacement for it with classic margarita which was ok.

We had asked for fish and chips but ended up with boiled fish.On correction, we did get fried fish but it was like fish bonda !!!.

The second order for desserts took a while to arrive.

Overall the experience was okayish. But some of the food items we ordered, was impressive and would like visit again for the same.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  The food is pretty good. We have the basket of assorted chips/ fries.. and surprising to my liking all the varieties tastes different for a change. Also had the salad which was full of flavours. The set up is Rich and nicely done!!'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  We were hear for a pre-christmas lunch & chose the place since it featured a Christmas menu. I have been here before as well & found their food good. The ambience is a London style pub feel & they have an open air seating as well. We ordered from their Christmas menu & the starter of a stuffed potato jacket was exorbitantly priced compared to the portion sizes. The taste was pretty ordinary too. The drinks were good especially the buter beer & sangria. The Christmas specialty dessert Yule log from the expensive Christmas menu was the second thing that was satisfactory, of not portion size wise or taste wise, but had a wonderful presentation. For the main course we ordered a roasted chicken which was again ordinary. Overall a pricey affair with average food experience.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Simply love the way this place is beautifully setup. Though the food menu is strictly limited the meltingpot(veg) and sourdough fondue (nonveg) from community eats section were my favorites. Also, the burgers never fails to impress me.
The cocktails are bang on strong and just the right taste.
Though the music is quite loud most of the times.
Good service by the courteous staff.'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  It's nice ambience and nice views, talking about service we order chicken Nachos but we got veg Nachos, i called service guys and inform him but he said we order veg, its k fine, and 2nd think he didn't repeat my order,,,, 3rd think they didn't ask for water??? 4th think no one asking about food?? Like how's ur food or drinks etc.,,,
We heard there food was tasty , dsty we want there, but food was okay, but not to much good. Otherwise amazing ambience."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Went here a while back and thought the ambience was nice the food was average and the music too loud so having a conversation with friend is difficult'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Situated in VR Mall, this place looks very English. You can see multiple clocks hung all around the place. It adds a very rich look to it.

Coming to the most important part - food!
We ordered chicken pizza, beer roasted chicken and a fish item. The pizza was very delicious!
The roasted chicken and fish wasn't tasty at all except for the sauce used. The meat did not seem so fresh and tender. It tasted like it was in the freezer for quiet sometime before it was cooked.

I was personally not satisfied with the food.

Staff were friendly and served food on time. They have happy hours before 8PM and we got complimentary drinks.

Zomato gold has been one of the best thing on this app and we unlocked the food offer here. :-) some discount is not bad after all for a foodie :-D

I probably may not want to visit this place again."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Perfect place to enjoy a few drinks after your shopping spree. The ambience is similar to other Irish House Pubs across the country. Service and food is great. Their burgers are Kickass and I actually fell in love with their mushroom burger - big achievement for a non veg lover like me.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Been to this place of a Friday noon. It was all empty barring a few customers. The first thing that catches the eye is the interiors which are kind of unique. We ordered for one wheat bear along with nachos and paneer corn sticks. While I loved the Paneer my better half felt nachos were good. The presentation was unique and the music not too loud.. We took high chairs which were a little bit conjusted to have your food.. The menu is not very huge but unique and someone took the effort to display the pictures next to the menu which makes choice easier for veg guys like me.
All in all its a nice place to go.. If you love wheat beer please try their tap beer and not the bottled one. You won't regret."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  The beer is not the only good bit here. Beautiful menu with finger food that makes you drool.
Particularly good are the grilled fish and roast chicken. The Xmas menu is enticing but limited.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Went here on a Saturday evening and the place was alive with great music, a cheerful atmosphere and good food. We had the cajun sweet potato fries and the fried tasted pretty good with a distinct taste.

The real winner for me was one of the cocktails. It's called winter's call and it's perfect when you're having a cold. I had this and the drink literally transported me to a Nordic town that's cold with hints of apples and cinnamon around. This was a delightful drink, also strong! Will definitely be visiting soon again."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This pub is situated inside VR mall. We went here on a Thursday night. Food was so tasty. We tried pizza here and no doubt it was so yummy. They have good options for cocktails as well. Interior was so attractive that you will feel one big city pub kind of. They have some outside sitting as well. You will definitely enjoy this place especially on weekends night.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Irish house is our go to place, more for office parties, as it is spacious and had a very wide variety of food and beverages.
I have visited Irish house a million times and it never ceases to keep up with the quality and taste of the food served.
For a change, this time I went with a friend and ordered a couple of my favourite things. I do wish we had bigger tummies because we did miss onto a couple of my favourites cz it was just 2 of us!

I love :
Crunchy Mini tacos with BBQ chicken
Cheese burst chicken
Fries with good old Mac n cheese
Smoked chicken pita pockets
Drunk meatballs
Two face chicken skewers
Belfast glazed chicken wings
Hummus platter
Herbivores basket (so much variety)
Grande nachos
Irish Riverdance
Dual chocolate torte

A couple of mocktails like chili guava.

I would say it is a bit pricy but totally worth the money because the food is very very yum!
I rest my case.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  The beer is not the only good bit here. Beautiful menu with finger food that makes you drool.
Particularly good are the grilled fish and roast chicken. The Xmas menu is enticing but limited.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Went here on a Saturday evening and the place was alive with great music, a cheerful atmosphere and good food. We had the cajun sweet potato fries and the fried tasted pretty good with a distinct taste.

The real winner for me was one of the cocktails. It's called winter's call and it's perfect when you're having a cold. I had this and the drink literally transported me to a Nordic town that's cold with hints of apples and cinnamon around. This was a delightful drink, also strong! Will definitely be visiting soon again."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  This pub is situated inside VR mall. We went here on a Thursday night. Food was so tasty. We tried pizza here and no doubt it was so yummy. They have good options for cocktails as well. Interior was so attractive that you will feel one big city pub kind of. They have some outside sitting as well. You will definitely enjoy this place especially on weekends night.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Irish house is our go to place, more for office parties, as it is spacious and had a very wide variety of food and beverages.
I have visited Irish house a million times and it never ceases to keep up with the quality and taste of the food served.
For a change, this time I went with a friend and ordered a couple of my favourite things. I do wish we had bigger tummies because we did miss onto a couple of my favourites cz it was just 2 of us!

I love :
Crunchy Mini tacos with BBQ chicken
Cheese burst chicken
Fries with good old Mac n cheese
Smoked chicken pita pockets
Drunk meatballs
Two face chicken skewers
Belfast glazed chicken wings
Hummus platter
Herbivores basket (so much variety)
Grande nachos
Irish Riverdance
Dual chocolate torte

A couple of mocktails like chili guava.

I would say it is a bit pricy but totally worth the money because the food is very very yum!
I rest my case.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Visited with my friends...had a good time...

Service 4/5

Food: 4/5 - The spread of the menu is quite good here. The food we ordered was tasty and looked delicious. Check the pics

Ambiance: 4/5 - option of indoor and outdoor seating. Comfortable seats. The inside portion looks really nice.

Service: 4/5 - service was really good. Courteous staff.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We went here for team lunch. It has great interiors and good ambience. The food was too good. We ordered pan crust chicken pizza, shrimp tacos, drunk mutton balls, cheese burst chicken, smoked chicken pita pockets, the Irish lion chicken tenders, Belfast glaced chicken wings, herbivores basket, chicken grande nachos, grilled fish, spinach and cheese jammers. We also ordered drinks - tangerine moijito, melon brainfreeze. My personal favourites among the lot were cheese burst chicken, drunken mutton balls, chicken grande nachos and spinach and cheese jammers. It was a great food experience. The staff were courteous. The Bellandur outlet has zomato gold as well. I will definitely go back to this restaurant again and again.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Apparently, the decor and ambiance gives you European and Irish feel. Outdoor and Indoor seating both are available.

Appetizers are quite different and nice.
Cheese Chicken burst is yum and you will crave for more Mac and cheese pasta everytime.

I like Weiss Guy beer. They have decent range of drinks. Go ahead and get irishy drunk.

Service is quick.

Ambiance : 5/5
Service:4/5
Food:4.5/5

Get irishy drunk :)'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  An evening very well spent..What an ambience and decor!! Loved the decor...amazing place to be with friends and family...

Staffs are trained,friendly and polite. Prompt service...they plays some awesome music...Good crowd on weekends...

  It is located in second floor of Phoenix marketcity mall in Whitefield. The place is nice and cosy with indoor and outdoor seating area overlooking the bustling courtyard.

Having been to other restro bars of Harry's, we had certain expectations. However, to be honest, we were a bit disappointed.

Coming to bar nibbles , we went for crispy chicken, Andhra chicken pepper fry and drunken chicken. To begin with, the crispy chicken was weirdly dissatisfying. Andhra pepper chicken was too salty with soggy gravy which wasn't going well with the drinks. Drunken chicken was okayish, better as compared to the other two.
Harry's needs to improve on serving consistent food across.

The drinks were okay though. We took long legged Peggy, Himalayan mule and few shots of Smirnoff . Drinks seem to be the only saving grace.

All in all, Ambience, service and drinks fare well."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  In an increasingly overcrowded mall pub space, Bar Bar is a breath of fresh air with it's draught beer, amazing pizzas, interesting finger food, karaoke nights, all coupled with great service at a well worth it price point. It's become our new go to at Phoenix - with most restaurants increasing their prices and decreasing portions, Bar Bar has managed to keep a good balance and always play the best music too!"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A comfy setup perfect for brunch or date nights. The beer menu had many options but the availability was slightly limited. The food however, perfect! Super fresh and filled with flavours. The pizzas were served hot, straight from the oven, thin crust and yum! The starters were good too.   A lovely ambience at the Bar Bar, located inside Phoenix Market City Mall. It has both outdoor and indoor seating options. Their in-house DJ plays a good playlist on weekends, which will make you move to it's beats. You can choose to order:

Peri Peri Chicken Sausages: Served with Potato Wedges, the chicken pieces were soft and a little on the spicy side because of the sauce.

Classic Margherita Pizza: They made it just as it was supposed to be. It's a thin crust pizza with a good taste of cheese.

virtuaniz.com"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

  Loved the ambience! The lights at the bar counter look simple and elegant.

I believe they have karaoke nights too, not sure which day of the week. They even have a foosball table for a quick game.

The food was not upto expectations, nevertheless it wasn't bad either, considering I have eaten better elsewhere. The pricing is similar to many other bars and pubs across the city.

Overall I had a nice time. I will recommend this place to others."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  We had ordered, Mac n Cheese burger, Nachos, jalapeno poppers and Pasta. Totally in love with Mac n Cheese burger. It was so tasty. Quantity was good enough. Totally enjoyed the meal. Must try.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I visited this place in evening so it was quiet. The outdoor sitting area is good and offers a good view to the stage set outside in front of the mall. Service was prompt.

We tried spiced guava and chocolate Oreo shake for beverages. Both of them were amazing. The shake was the right amount of thick.
We had sun-dried tomatoes and white onions pizza. It was delicious. The sauce was tangy enough but not too much. The crust was crispy and the pizza wasn't a mess like the ones with too many toppings.
Barbecue cottage cheese chunks were good as well. Everything on the plate went together very well."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  We went out to this place little late on Friday evening... We got the table outside which literally gave us the feeling as if we are no where in the restaurant.
We asked them to shift us inside as soon as any table is available, but despite table being available they couldn't manage that.

Service was very very slow... For every order we have to remind them multiple times... Even for beer I don't k ow why do take lot of time.

  A good place to dine. Very friendly staff and the management as well. Food is good too. Ambience is soothing and the music is a great add on to that place. Plus they screen matches as well which is great for a sports fan.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This place is huge! Fooled by the entrance, I didnt expect the place to be large. No issues finding a table :P

The service here is good, we were well attended to and the servers kept a good eye on the water levels in our glass. The food however took some time to get ready after order.

They have a good selection of food, I liked the food here. Alcohol here is reasonably priced. Bacon was a let down though, it was very salty.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Went to this place on Sunday afternoon it was empty. We were the only guest available there. Food was great and Alcoholic drinks had one plus one offer.
We asked for Axis bank discount of 15% as mentioned in the Zomato application but they refused. Apart from this it was great place to hang out.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  We went to this place for sort of after party, from some nearby place. We didn't ate much...had beers and french fries.
When we entered, we sort of liked this place majorly coz of some open space and live music; but then service here was pathetic..we have to wait for more than 10 mins just for someone to attend us and take order and it seemed that waiters were least bothered about it.

I wanted to give this place 2/5; but then just coz I liked the atmosphere and live music...I am going with 3/5."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

  What started as a good evening ended as an average experience! These guys need a tutorial on customer service!"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  I only look for good food and courteous staff because I think everything else depends on your company. So, its fist bump for both these qualities for this place. I ordered Cheese balls, garlic cheese poppers, beer battered onion rings for the starters plus Peach and Passion fruit Iced tea.

  A place where you really want to hop around with your friends and chill out. I went here at Saturday night and yes it was amazing for me. Good food and a music made us all set and I really enjoyed a lot with my friends.
#foodiesapien
Follow me on youtube : Foodie Sapien
Instagram : manishpushkar'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Visited this place on a Saturday late evening. From the outside though there is a huge hoarding and everything it totally doesn't prepare you for what's in store inside. The place is quite massive with huge seating area. It's a good place for watching matches too as there are a couple of giant screens there. We (a group of 5) got a place almost immediately on reaching and let me tell you that place was quite crowded but it's the widespread seating area that made it possible. For food we tried a couple of starters both of which were good. Coming to drinks we stuck to the age old cocktails. Whiskey sour and liit. Both of which were concentrated and one of them was enough to get you buzzed. The staff was prompt and helpful as well.
Overall a good experience.
Hoping to try out more from the food menu the next time I visit. FridayÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x99s can be an exception in terms of service due to the crazy crowds. I have had a couple of team dinners in PabloÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x99s with a very good package. My team enjoyed their evenings there.
A lovely place to be at on weekdays if you want a quiet and not very crowded place to hang out at.
P.S. The restrooms need to be checked at regular intervals.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I went to this place on a Saturday night. This place looks huge and has a good ambience, unfortunately it wasn't a happening place. There were less people at the gastrobar. The drinks were just fine. The slow motion cocktail was very different from the description. They also have hookah. The beer battered onion rings were good but their chilli chicken wasn't good and the chicken was pretty hard."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Among my best dinner experiences in Bengaluru! And I don't think it would be changing any time soon. Of course the company matters, went here with my best buddies. But nothing to take away from the place.
The whole gastrobar has a great vibe to it with openness of the entire seating and karaoke on the side. The staff is really warm and friendly. The cheese samosas and potato jackets were great appetizers. The pizza was good too. The highlight of the whole evening was an extremely potent LIIT though ;)
The crowd too was lively adding to the entire experience. Overall a must visit place."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Perfect place to spend your weekend nights with karaoke on fridays, tasty food and amazing service! Have gone so many times and love it each time.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The place is nice but the ambience is a bit dull. it's near to my office so I have been there couple of times just because its nearby. The food is ok ok.
.
They have kareoke night on Fridays but they only allow English songs ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â°ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x98ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x91ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â°ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x98ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x91

column2: ITPL Ascendas Park Square Mall, ITPL, First Floor, ITPB, Whitefield Road, Bangalore,

column12: Finger Food, American, Continental, Burger, Pizza
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I had :-

1. Italian Tiramisu Shake
2. Grilled One's (Burgers) Chicken

Loved both the items... The shake was really good... It whet my appetite for the burger which too was lovely and delectable...

The staff was pleasant and friendly..."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Oliver's is always the place where people working in ITPL go if they are in mood to chill post work.
This place serves decent pizza and drinks"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I have been to this place couple of times now. Found it OK in terms of food, service, ambience, pricing and availability of drinks.
On our 1st visit we were around 6people and had ordered chicken starters, beer, wine and pizza. However, the service was too slow. Even the bill was given to us almost after 20mins of asking the waiters.
During 2nd visit, we were 5 people. This visit was bit disappointing, as almost 80% of the drinks on menu which I wanted to have were not available. Ultimately i had to get a diet coke. Even the food menu is a traditional one. There is nothing different and the taste is average.
My friend also tried flame shot here, which was a big disappointment as the waiters who made it seemed amateurs. He had struggled so much to drink that flame shot, as the flame was all over the table.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I'm pleasantly surprised when I happen to find new places to dine close to home.
With this in mind I stopped by Oliver a while back. 
Overlooking ITPL, the atmosphere here is well lit and lively especially if you happen to be here during live match screenings. 
Coming to the food I was a bit disappointed. 
I ordered the buenos nachos and the chicken nachos pizza. 
Talking about the nachos, they were basically made with cornitos chips. 
The crust of the pizza was dry and the toppings lacked seasoning. 
The drinks we ordered were just okayish.
Overall slightly disappointed."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered chilly pork, which was not really very spicy( also most of the pieces were pork fat only and not meat) . And the noodles was good but not that good. Kind of expected a little bit more from this place. Found it a bit overpriced for the quantity.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Good place to hang out and chill with your friends with good food and drinks. You would love their range of pizzas and their taste if you like thin crush pizzas - like the Mexican nachos one myself. Drinks are good too with offers - mainly people opt for Bira. Had sizzling Brownie in desserts and it was yum! Can improve more on overall crust and taste of the pizzas though - not that nice if you're going only for food. ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9cÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x8cÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â°ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x8fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â» #ThinCrustPizzas #Bira"), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Visited during lunch hours.
The nachos were pretty filling but just about above-average in taste.

I would recommend the Gambas! Prawns were succelent and flavourful.

The service was also pretty quick. I'm not sure why the stools were a little worn out and the ambience was a little low and dim. Perhaps the aim was to give a rusty vibe but the tables and chairs seemed a little too old and rusted."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  It's one of the few places we found open past 9pm near ITPL, that serves cocktails. It's on the first floor of the shopping complex. This one cocktail called Hanky Panky was particularly good."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Oliver's.. The place i love for pizzas... And hey.. If you want to just chill, have some beer along with your friends then this is the place for you.. I personally love their pizzas and the ambience.. Cheers..!!"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Oliver's have been a go to place after office as it is in ITPL itself. For drinks they don't keep much options available which is disappointing. Coming to food, food is really good. We tried chilly chicken, American corn and crispy babycorn for starters and had chilly paneer tikka and spinach paneer pizza. Taste and ambience is very much lively and dewy."), ('Rated 1.0', "RATED
  This restaurant was a big disappointment. The list of unprofessionalism is quite big.
We found a dead cockroach near the table. And when pointing it out the service guy was least bothered and asked some other guy to look into it.Then we shifted to a different table.
Another downer was the unresponsive attitude of the staff. We literally had to get up from our seats to give order.
The food was above par to it's service, which was a good thing. But when some one visits ur restaurant, they want to have the full dining experience. Otherwise food can be home delivered.
Please work on ur cleanliness and service if u want to attract customers."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  A desi styled pub easy on pocket, still under construction. Has got combo offers throughout the week. The food is great to hangout on any day of the week. Should minimise the order delivery time.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Tasty food at not so high rates. The ambience and service was pretty good.

We had spring rolls and jalapeno poppers for starters. They didn't feel too oily and were delicious. Sauces served with them went pretty well with them.

We went for patata salsa pizza. Potato part tasted good. Though I would have liked better sauce.

For desserts, we went for brownie sundae and it was amazing. The quantity was generous as well."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Not sure why it is rated so high on Zomato. When I go to any pub I expect atleast some good quality finger food and mocktails. Both were missing here. Service was way below par as the servers didn't even know what to recommend and what is house special etc. Pizza was OK.

Ambience wise a good place to hang out with friends and make some noise. They did try to make it look like a sports bar with TV screens here and there. But failed miserably.

Overall experience was well below par."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Good place for stress busting.ambience is friendly.bug food quality is not upto the mark.beer also not available according to your choice.we asked Bira..they told it's not available right now (seriously?? Even on Saturday evening).Music was ok only..not a good music place.the only advantage I got is its in ITPL ,beside my office."), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  Pathetic presentation of the dishes, the plate looks half empty. It's just cigarette smoke that u can breath.
Did not enjoy the food or ambience."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Went there on a Friday eve. They were out of almost every good branded beers. Below average food, the place seems a little bit shady. Sitting chairs and tables are really rusty. Staffs not really pro active in serving you. They overcharged me, had to call them and get the amount back. So you get the picture.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Oliver's Pub is a decent place with a good ambience. Food was pretty good although we tried only vegetarian dishes. They had limited options for drinks and few of the listed drinks were not even available. I had the most amazing Chinese bhel over here. I tried two variants of pizzas there : Paneer peri peri and Margherita paneer spinach pizza, both of them were nicely made. Please do give a try to the spinach one. [('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Like this place for zomato gold 2+2 on drinks . Whenever in Phoenix , just head up to this place , enjoy some nice cocktails . We took the bar platter which was equally good .'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  This is a place to be for fun, bowling and games.

column2: Lemon Tree Hotel, 23, EPIP Zone, Near I Gate Company, Whitefield, Bangalore
MGM Mark Whitefield, 23, EPIP Zone, Whitefield, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Staying at the MGM Whitefield and this place is good enough to just unwind after a hectic day at work. Limited options for liquor though and the bar attendant is extremely courteous. Service is topnotch but the liquor menu can be improved. Absence of draught beer is a big minus. The chilli paneer and chicken pudina tikka is a must order.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  We went here for breakfast. It has a pretty good variety, but not as much as some other breakfast buffets. It does have something for everyone, though, for the most part. You get a buffet with breads, coffee, a wide range of teas, chai, boiled vegetables, cereal, idlis, dosa, poha, fruits, and a live counter. They also served pancakes with maple syrup on request. 

It's overall a pretty good buffet where you can calmly eat and gather your thoughts, but it isn't for the casual foodie. They insist on serving you at your table and suggest you on different ways to try out the food (who knew you could put curd and half a dozen things on poha?) People who stay at the hotel or have come for a business meeting will find this an ideal place to sit and talk. A nice place, at least for breakfast, but it could do with improvement."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  " If unwinding in style is what you are looking for than this place is sure to transport you into realm of relaxation and ease with its chic ambience and soothing music."

That's what the description I read online before heading for this place. To be frank I would say - Not Exactly.

No question about the ease part as there is absolutely no one else inside other than you, your gang and the hotel staff. Probably because its situated inside the MGM marks hotel, behind the Lemon tree hotel.

Although the service people are good and descent and the place seems great, yet it all seems dull without people in it.

Hope you find a better experience in terms of liveliness.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  This is not a pure veg restaurant. I called there and confirmed before leaving to this place.')]

column3: The Farm House Bar n Grill
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ambience- Big and spacious lawn was used to host new year event including unlimited food, drinks, dj, dholak performance, firedance and belly dance.

Pocket friendly- Reasonable for the services offered.

Food- Veg and Non veg starters were served hot and had plenty of options including Fish and Chicken. The dishes could have been less oily.

In drinks you had plenty of options for alcoholic drinks but only 3 non alcoholic drinks which was dissapointing.

Main course had good variety of Breads, Salads, Rice Items, Curries in both veg and nonveg. Desserts had plenty of options to choose from apart from the regular ones.

Service- Quick and prompt considering the crowd. The bar could have been better managed for non alcoholic section.

Rating- 4 for the awsome experience.')]

It was extremely hot and suffocating experience. We were a group of around 40. Starters served was broccoli with veg cutlet. It was made terribly and I believe that it is the cause of food poisoning that I experienced the immediate night. The welcome drink, cranberry mock tail on the other hand was an absolute delight. We had dal makhani and paneer veg gravies which were OK ok. The dessert was rasmalai, ice cream and gulab jamun with nothing special in taste. What would have a been wonderful night turned out to be very mediocre owing to the food served here. Menu is very small.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  This was long time due, was planning to experience Taj hotel Mumbai but couldn't go there for some reasons hence convinced ourself atleast to treat ourself here post new year. After a tiring adventurous ride from Belgaum to Bangalore we went for a dinner in the evening at Tease. This place is next to itpl bangalore, prominent place. Got a warm welcome by their staff, they directed us to the restaurant, got valet parking. Tease has got very nice ambience, We took a poolside table. The staff got us the complimentary snacks & menu. We ordered some mocktails & cocktail along with buffalo wings. Enjoyed their ambience for sometime got our food & drink. Mocktail & cocktail was awesome but buffalo wings was not cooked well & they have put some dark black sauce which was not edible. Hence we don't wanted to try anything else here."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  After the attached review written previously, appreciate that Mr Manjit called and took a detailed feedback. I hope Tease lives up to Taj service at all times. The ambience and food is good!'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The Tease Lounge is located above the lobby level, it has a very pleasant ambiance, spacious with a reflective water body leading all the way to the Bar. The open-air seating offers a great view of the Technology Park with landscaped lawns. It is a great relaxation from the hustle-bustle of city life and is really soothing.

Went over with my wife one evening and we really enjoyed the fresh Coconut Crusted Prawns - King Size Prawns cooked in coconut, it was very well fried and was served with sauces that were just as Awesome as the Prawns. Would definitely recommend trying out the Coconut Crusted Prawns.

The Mock-tail - Doctor's Advice was good but could have been better by way of bringing out the flavors of the blend of Guava nectar, mango juice muddled with Rose Water and Lime containing fresh Cucumber pieces.

The overall service was very good."), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED

  Beautiful place to spend if you are looking for a quiet evening on a weekday. They have landscaping around, with outdoor & indoor seating. They have sofas like seating indoor & bean bags outside. Cocktails are very nicely done with everything in the right proportion. I would definitely recommend this place for a weekday visit & definitely not for a weekend visit as they play really loud music during the weekends & refuse to reduce the volume even when asked for. 

Do try their margherita pizza with basil & hot toddy if you have a bad throat. :)'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

  Food and service are incomparably excellent. The service staff are attentive, polite, and always willing to go the extra mile to help. Sovon and Girish (pictured) are friendly and always helpful. I am here long term and I'm happy to have such an amazing group taking care of me."), ('Rated 3.5', "RATED
  Decent food. Small Cody place. Can't complaint much cuz we got a good deal with Nearby. Their satay chicken is a must try. Peanut sauce was perfect. Good food, good service. But it lacks the vibe."), ('Rated 2.5', 'RATED

column2: Keys Hotel, 1st Phase Industrial Area, Near Graphite India, Whitefield, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Thank you Biju P for taking good care of me during my chill out times.

I really like the courtesy shown by Biju considering that I am all by myself during visit. He added some extra bit to make my visit special ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â°ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x9fÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x98ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x8a
Once again thank you so much.

I was so happy with how I was made to feel special as a stay home guest that I forgot the food review.

I ordered Big Bite Burger and I must say that I really like it and the sides. Thank you for good food!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Good place to unwind and have a nice laid back time. The staff are very friendly and happy accept special requests. I stayed at the hotel for 15 days and hence the restaurant was my default go-to place. Marginally on the expensive side but thatÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚Ã‚Â¢ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x80ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x83ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x83ÃƒÂ‚\x82ÃƒÂƒ\x82ÃƒÂ‚\x99s understandable for a hotel with accommodation.'), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  I guess you are here to know how good or bad it is. Well, to begin with the bar has some nice aesthetics and that's about it.Nothing out of the world. The staff is super nice which more or lezst makes up for the averageness of the place. Overall I would say "just another place to hangout".
I rest my case. Peace!'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Had been to keys again yesterday. This si probably the most economical and best bar in the whitefield belt. the startes take time to come but its worth the wait. they serve everything from beer to mocktails to coktails and the bar is always packed on weekends. They also have a pool table to play in the bar. I will keep coming her again. Need to give me some discounts pls. lol. c u guys soon.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Bad.Not gonna go back ever.Ambience staff behaviour ,starters all are poor given that they have bit pricier menu.Order being delayed and no staff available around you for more than 15 mins.You have to keep waiving your hands so rhat they notice you.Finally had to stand up and then chased one to listen to my order.bad xperience.'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  A place not meant for drinking or hanging out with friends.
Pathetic service and they serve warm beer.. was very disappointed ...
There are better places to hang around n the same rate'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Went there to attend a kid's birthday party and liked it.
Good decor with spacious hall and seating area. Decent service.
Now the food part - they had quite variety of food in the buffet. I loved one chicken preparation which was, I suppose, some south Indian style - with drum sticks and flavor of curry leaves. Refreshing taste. Other items were average or above. Vegetarian dishes were better than the non-veg ones.
Overall good experience."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  I found this place pretty relaxing..very comfortable ambience, cosy place..bar counter well lighted and decorated....have order black dog scotch to ease my full day tiredness and traveling...had fish tikka which was awesome.....felt nice and had relaxing time....do visit here for a drink with small group of friends...'), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Unlock is a casual yet good place. Play station and the pool table added to the god experience, for me being a fan of both.
Food was just okay, looked like it was taken and served from the buffet in the other seating area. Rotis/Naans were elastic and cold. When we went there, a team dinner for some 20-25 people was already booked. So the staff was really struggling to manage other tables, which kept us going to waiters directly for any assistance.')]

column2: Fortune Select Trinity, 134/136, EPIP Area Road-1, Whitefield, Bangalore
column14:
[('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  Had a breakfast buffet here. Quite expensive though but the English breakfast was quite good.
Had a experience of classic English breakfast like beacons, baked beans etc.
Nothing special, just for those people who wants to spend money on some not so healthy English breakfast.'), ('Rated 2.0', 'RATED
  Place is meant for corporate outings. You can very well imagine the quality of food, ambience etc about the place where they organise corporate parties.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I was invited to this place last Wednesday for lunch where the lunch was served as a buffet and it had Veg Pulav, Indian Bread with Paneer Butter Masala gravy and Kerala Special Gravy which was prepared with Cauliflower and Carrot. The Pulav was above average in taste and Indian Bread was okay. Whereas Paneer Butter Masala gravy was good. Along with this there was rice, dal, rasam and curd rice. I think I don't have to explain the taste of these as it tastes the same where ever we visit. Last but not the least, the sweet served was Moong Dal Halwa which was totally amazing in taste and I seriously don't have words to define the taste of it so let me quickly add few pics. The place was amazingly breathtaking and beautiful, great hospitality as well."), ('Rated 3.5', 'RATED
  Very average place, no loud music and in middle of Whitefield with not many people in evening makes it a good place for taking couple of drinks with office buddies or colleagues. Sometimes they have good offers too which makes it even better.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  We had our annual party here. They have a well maintained lawn; open to air ambience. That's were our event was planned. Chilled beer n soft drinks were served at one end.. Buffet dinner was also good. Best place for office party.. Service also is good."), ('Rated 4.5', 'RATED
  Brlliant place to go out with old friends. Good music, beer and food. A full package.'), ('Rated 3.5', "RATED
  This place is really a good joint for drinks and snacks to go along with it, right opposite to SAP labs is fortune Hotel and this is their Coffee shop adjoining their lobby.
Though the hotel has a restaurant too, but if you are looking for just a couple of glasses to cool you down and you are in the vicinity and don't want to travel much then you can definitely try this place out, though you have many other options in the vicinity @ the same price point"), (None, 'I am a regular to this hotel since the past few years but it is sad to see the quality of food consistently dropping as in my other review BUT was very nice today to get freash draught fosters at the lounge, have not seen in Whitefield and that too buy 1 get 1 complimentary, very nice prawn and snacks
Great service, only needs more privacy'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  what a shame , the buffet was awfully miserable for vegetarians.')]

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Nice and friendly place and staff is awesome. Ansur and karaoke singer is too good and Friday nights are The best night to visit this place. Drinks and food menu as usual match the service'), ('Rated 1.0', 'RATED
  The service is bad. We ordered 4 Stella Artois and they gave us expired bottles. When we asked them to replace it they were reluctant about it and asked me to drink the same bottle. However they changed it later after hassle. They billed us for food which we didnt eat also. They said they will call later but no response.
Ordered food from Feast(their restaurant) and the quality was fine. Their paneer and daal were good but checken pizza was uncooked and soggy. Their non veg platter was amazing though. Their mocktails are below average.
Such kind of food and service is not expected from Sheraton.'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Nice bar inside Sheraton. The hosts are friendly and helpful, service is quick. You can use marriot rewards here to earn discount and rewards'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  My review based on food drink service

Service:- as usual hotel service I am personally like very much because they are more professional to their work so no bad thing I have found on their service thanks for good service they made my day

We will visit again I will suggest everyone to visit once"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  I visited chime bar at Sheraton hotel it was nice experience they making nice cocktail with nice food.i recommend to this hotel for visite and enjoy experience. Thanks to Ruben and amiya for service'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This restaurant is situated inside grand Sheraton hotel. This place is quite luxurious. Food quality and service are really high with a luxurious ambience. But this place is purely recommended for business lunch or dinner or for some high level party.')]

Talking about the food, we ordered sticky nachos, peanut masala and flat bread pizza.
