  Great Food and ambience .. Appreciate Staff Tahidul For some amazing Service . Baby corn , Crispy Chicken was awesome and Finger licking food .'), ('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  An over-rated restaurant that serves below average cocktails. We were skeptical to try out this place having read its mixed reviews. A decision gone wrong I must say. Nothing about this place or it's food had any positive about it. The starters had such menial quantity it was embarrassing.

You guys need to pull your socks up and provide a better experience to your customers."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Went to this happening place with friends.. it had loud music, a pool table and live football match was being played on a big screen.

We got a table quickly maybe bcoz of a Friday. Ordered few starters which were good. The DJ was good, he played some nice Bollywood tracks and we enjoyed dancing. Ordered main course which was not that great. Definitely can be improved.

Overall good!!

Food - 3/5
Service - 4/5
Ambience - 5/5
Cleanliness - 4/5
Pocket Friendly - 2/5

-With Shibin Varghese'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  We orderer an LIIT along with a chicken starter and BBq sloppy burger. The burger was really juicy and good. The chicken starter was ok. The ambiance was food, service was pretty fast. Will go back to try other items from the menu.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  It is located in second floor of Phoenix marketcity mall in Whitefield. The place is nice and cosy with indoor and outdoor seating area overlooking the bustling courtyard.

Having been to other restro bars of Harry's, we had certain expectations. However, to be honest, we were a bit disappointed.

Coming to bar nibbles , we went for crispy chicken, Andhra chicken pepper fry and drunken chicken. To begin with, the crispy chicken was weirdly dissatisfying. Andhra pepper chicken was too salty with soggy gravy which wasn't going well with the drinks. Drunken chicken was okayish, better as compared to the other two.
Harry's needs to improve on serving consistent food across.

The drinks were okay though. We took long legged Peggy, Himalayan mule and few shots of Smirnoff . Drinks seem to be the only saving grace.

All in all, Ambience, service and drinks fare well."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  The first thing that caught my attention was the pool table. A nice place to hang out with friends and have fun. A bit on the expensive side but delicious food and cocktails.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  If you love drinking and don't have that much budget left this is the place for you. The drinks are quite well priced and they give peanuts in packets which is the best thing I have seen in any pub. I just love visiting this place. Food is very good and LIIT is also good."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  In an increasingly overcrowded mall pub space, Bar Bar is a breath of fresh air with it's draught beer, amazing pizzas, interesting finger food, karaoke nights, all coupled with great service at a well worth it price point. It's become our new go to at Phoenix - with most restaurants increasing their prices and decreasing portions, Bar Bar has managed to keep a good balance and always play the best music too!"), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  A comfy setup perfect for brunch or date nights. The beer menu had many options but the availability was slightly limited. The food however, perfect! Super fresh and filled with flavours. The pizzas were served hot, straight from the oven, thin crust and yum! The starters were good too.   A lovely ambience at the Bar Bar, located inside Phoenix Market City Mall. It has both outdoor and indoor seating options. Their in-house DJ plays a good playlist on weekends, which will make you move to it's beats. You can choose to order:

Peri Peri Chicken Sausages: Served with Potato Wedges, the chicken pieces were soft and a little on the spicy side because of the sauce.

Classic Margherita Pizza: They made it just as it was supposed to be. It's a thin crust pizza with a good taste of cheese.

  Loved the ambience! The lights at the bar counter look simple and elegant.

I believe they have karaoke nights too, not sure which day of the week. They even have a foosball table for a quick game.

The food was not upto expectations, nevertheless it wasn't bad either, considering I have eaten better elsewhere. The pricing is similar to many other bars and pubs across the city.

Overall I had a nice time. I will recommend this place to others."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  We had ordered, Mac n Cheese burger, Nachos, jalapeno poppers and Pasta. Totally in love with Mac n Cheese burger. It was so tasty. Quantity was good enough. Totally enjoyed the meal. Must try.'), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  I visited this place in evening so it was quiet. The outdoor sitting area is good and offers a good view to the stage set outside in front of the mall. Service was prompt.

We tried spiced guava and chocolate Oreo shake for beverages. Both of them were amazing. The shake was the right amount of thick.
We had sun-dried tomatoes and white onions pizza. It was delicious. The sauce was tangy enough but not too much. The crust was crispy and the pizza wasn't a mess like the ones with too many toppings.
Barbecue cottage cheese chunks were good as well. Everything on the plate went together very well."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  We had a lovely lazy Sunday lunch in Bar Bar yesterday. We chose to get some sun and sit outside. We ordered a BBQ Chicken pizza and a Pesto Chicken along with some drinks. The pizza was delicious but the Pesto chicken was a little hard. But I enjoyed the perfectly made potato wedges more than the chicken itself. The staff was very courteous and helpful. 
The ambience was okish as there were not many people at that hour of the day. While leaving, we couldn't resist ourselves from playing a few foosball games as a table was set up right in front of the entrance."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Visited this place for dinner on a Saturday evening. We got a table fairly quickly. The ambience is beautiful, music is great, and the view lovely. We ordered Corn Tikki and Jalapeno and Cheese Popcorn as starters, along with Penne in Basil and Pesto sauce and Andhra Biryani. The taste and presentation of food was amazing. The staff was very courteous and quick to respond to all the requests. Overall, a great experience. Would love to visit the place again! :)'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED

  Great ambiance with delicious food. I went on Sunday noon , it was packed and took 10 mins to get the table. Weather was rainy that made the view really amazing .I ordered paneer tikka and veg biryani. Paneer was soft and beautifully cooked ,went well with mint chutney. Biryani had full punch of flavours unlike other restaurant's bland rice.
Tried their drinks which didn't dissapoint.Certainly visiting again to try more items.

Cheers !!"), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

[('Rated 2.0', "RATED
  We went out to this place little late on Friday evening... We got the table outside which literally gave us the feeling as if we are no where in the restaurant.
We asked them to shift us inside as soon as any table is available, but despite table being available they couldn't manage that.

Service was very very slow... For every order we have to remind them multiple times... Even for beer I don't k ow why do take lot of time.

We ordered few starters like veg nachos, peanut masala, pizza and chicken wings... Which was ok.. Nit bad and not very good also.

Overall rating.. 2/5"), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

  There's more to this place than just beer!
That's true.
I visited this place on a weekday for lunch and found it to be all empty and quite which is quite contrary to the buzzing environment I'm generally used on weekends. My order included:
Nachos for starters
Veg Platter(onion rings, spring rolls and honey chilli potatoes) for starters
Peppy Paneer pizza
Egg biryani for main course
I loved how the outer single layer of the egg was friend and make crispy,it was just perfect.
Portion was good and all the dishes were fresh n tasty.
Must visit!

  On a lazy sunday afternoon, I was craving for a good pizza..but most of my friends were out of town... I opened zomato and this restaurant just popped up.. I ordered chicken supreme pizza... oh boy! one of the best pizzas I have had.. thin crust, succulent chicken pieces generously strewn and wonderfully packed.. Thanks Beer Cafe for making such awesome pizzas and Thank you Zomato for delivering the same.. Will I order/visit again?? Ofcourse!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The ambiance was pretty cool. Ordered some of their pizza varieties which I didn't like much. Also had coke glass which again didn't feel even like the original one.. Not chilled. Of course, it's a beer cafe and I'm sure they would be providing nice beer and definitely the ambiance is something that one would wanna go there."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Beer cafe located to vr mall, Whitefield. Its my favourite place to hangout with my friends, outside setting area is nice, but lots of mosquito, you cant seat outside but indoor its nice, food was good, talking bout service we are not happy for service , we called 2 or 3 times, i don't know where they will busy, they didn't came, after that my friend called again that time one guy is came nd took my order, overall all is fine."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Went for a quick bite n drinks...was planning to go from long time, n finally made it..the place is small n nice...I found the sitting arrangements really conjusted...too much crowded at Sunday night..waited for 10 to 15 mins to get a table...Good thing about the place is they take orders till late night...

Well coming to the food...food options is not much...we ordered chicken nachos n barbeque chicken wings with some beer...food taste was average not that great..

Service is very slow..no one is interested to take the orders...no one there to serve water also...kitchen was also too slow...have to wait for half n hr for getting food...really annoying...n on the top of that you will not see any service guys around...

Overall an okay experience...dint like their service at all...'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  They have Geist on Tap, lovely selection of beer and and both indoor and Outdoor seating, including a smoking area.  For me, the food here is a big surprise and pretty darn good. Everything I had here impressed me, including the quantity and taste. I would never imagine having a Biryani at a pub, but I did try it here, and Voila, it was really yummy.

Do try the beer braised trio chicken, the hariyali chicken tangri and the calcutta style chilli chicken, You will not regret it. Add Zomato Gold to that, and you have a winner!

theuncliched.com'), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED
  Amazing food. The food is so appealing and tasty that it will get over with few minutes. Must try tgere chicken nachos amazing. The ambiance is nice. Suited both for friends and family. Too good beer.'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  #Best place for hangout with friends. Specially in weekend.
Service is good. But I didn't like their beer taste. So I think they have to give good quality beer.
Staters quality and quantity was super. I had tried nacos . If you like then you try it."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  The kitchen is slow on a Sunday Night, with any food item taking about more than 30 mins, the servers appear helpless in this situation.

Chilli Paneer - don't recommend not cooked well.Dahi Pakoda - this was decent and worth a try.
Beer as always is good."), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  The ambience of the place is good. You have outdoor as well as indoor seatings available.
Coming to the service and staff, it is great and the staff is quite friendly.
For drinks, we ordered a mug of Budweiser. One of the best beers we have had. Pretty chilled and tasted amazing.
For food, we ordered a plate of veg nachos and hariyali chicken tangri. Both of them were good.

This is the go-to place if you're tired and really want to chill."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  The Beer Cafe probably has one of the largest selections of bottled beers. Their courtyard seating is always buzzing with activity. The interior seating however seems a little crammed especially so with the tables close to the door.

I was happy to see the Geist craft beer. It was refreshing and cold. We just wanted some bar food to go with the beer. The classic wings had a vinegary sourness to them and the calcutta chilli chicken had a strong dose of ketchup.

Ambiance 4/5
Food 2/5
Beer 4/5
Beer Selection 5/5
Service 3/5'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A good place to dine. Very friendly staff and the management as well. Food is good too. Ambience is soothing and the music is a great add on to that place. Plus they screen matches as well which is great for a sports fan.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  This place is huge! Fooled by the entrance, I didnt expect the place to be large. No issues finding a table :P

The service here is good, we were well attended to and the servers kept a good eye on the water levels in our glass. The food however took some time to get ready after order.

They have a good selection of food, I liked the food here. Alcohol here is reasonably priced. Bacon was a let down though, it was very salty.'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Went to this place on Sunday afternoon it was empty. We were the only guest available there. Food was great and Alcoholic drinks had one plus one offer.
We asked for Axis bank discount of 15% as mentioned in the Zomato application but they refused. Apart from this it was great place to hang out.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  We went to this place for sort of after party, from some nearby place. We didn't ate much...had beers and french fries.
When we entered, we sort of liked this place majorly coz of some open space and live music; but then service here was pathetic..we have to wait for more than 10 mins just for someone to attend us and take order and it seemed that waiters were least bothered about it.

I wanted to give this place 2/5; but then just coz I liked the atmosphere and live music...I am going with 3/5."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED

  What started as a good evening ended as an average experience!   I only look for good food and courteous staff because I think everything else depends on your company. So, its fist bump for both these qualities for this place. I ordered Cheese balls, garlic cheese poppers, beer battered onion rings for the starters plus Peach and Passion fruit Iced tea.
For main course, I ordered Spanish rice with paneer steak. Everything was yum, exactly how I like it. Give it a guys!!'), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  A place where you really want to hop around with your friends and chill out. I went here at Saturday night and yes it was amazing for me. Good food and a music made us all set and I really enjoyed a lot with my friends.
#foodiesapien
Follow me on youtube : Foodie Sapien
Instagram : manishpushkar'), ('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  Visited this place on a Saturday late evening. From the outside though there is a huge hoarding and everything it totally doesn't prepare you for what's in store inside. The place is quite massive with huge seating area. It's a good place for watching matches too as there are a couple of giant screens there. We (a group of 5) got a place almost immediately on reaching and let me tell you that place was quite crowded but it's the widespread seating area that made it possible. For food we tried a couple of starters both of which were good. Coming to drinks we stuck to the age old cocktails. Whiskey sour and liit. Both of which were concentrated and one of them was enough to get you buzzed. The staff was prompt and helpful as well.

  I went to this place on a Saturday night. This place looks huge and has a good ambience, unfortunately it wasn't a happening place. There were less people at the gastrobar. The drinks were just fine. The slow motion cocktail was very different from the description. They also have hookah. The beer battered onion rings were good but their chilli chicken wasn't good and the chicken was pretty hard."), ('Rated 5.0', "RATED
  Among my best dinner experiences in Bengaluru! And I don't think it would be changing any time soon. Of course the company matters, went here with my best buddies. But nothing to take away from the place.
The whole gastrobar has a great vibe to it with openness of the entire seating and karaoke on the side. The staff is really warm and friendly. The cheese samosas and potato jackets were great appetizers. The pizza was good too. The highlight of the whole evening was an extremely potent LIIT though ;)
The crowd too was lively adding to the entire experience. Overall a must visit place."), ('Rated 4.0', 'RATED

column14:
[('Rated 4.0', "RATED
  I had :-

1. Italian Tiramisu Shake
2. Grilled One's (Burgers) Chicken

Loved both the items... The shake was really good... It whet my appetite for the burger which too was lovely and delectable...

The staff was pleasant and friendly..."), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Oliver's is always the place where people working in ITPL go if they are in mood to chill post work.
This place serves decent pizza and drinks"), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  I have been to this place couple of times now. Found it OK in terms of food, service, ambience, pricing and availability of drinks.
On our 1st visit we were around 6people and had ordered chicken starters, beer, wine and pizza. However, the service was too slow. Even the bill was given to us almost after 20mins of asking the waiters.
During 2nd visit, we were 5 people. This visit was bit disappointing, as almost 80% of the drinks on menu which I wanted to have were not available. Ultimately i had to get a diet coke. Even the food menu is a traditional one. There is nothing different and the taste is average.
My friend also tried flame shot here, which was a big disappointment as the waiters who made it seemed amateurs. He had struggled so much to drink that flame shot, as the flame was all over the table.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  I'm pleasantly surprised when I happen to find new places to dine close to home.
With this in mind I stopped by Oliver a while back. 
Overlooking ITPL, the atmosphere here is well lit and lively especially if you happen to be here during live match screenings. 
Coming to the food I was a bit disappointed. 
I ordered the buenos nachos and the chicken nachos pizza. 
Talking about the nachos, they were basically made with cornitos chips. 
The crust of the pizza was dry and the toppings lacked seasoning. 
The drinks we ordered were just okayish.
Overall slightly disappointed."), ('Rated 3.0', 'RATED
  Ordered chilly pork, which was not really very spicy( also most of the pieces were pork fat only and not meat) . And the noodles was good but not that good. Kind of expected a little bit more from this place. Found it a bit overpriced for the quantity.'), ('Rated 3.0', "RATED
  Good place to hang out and chill with your friends with good food and drinks. You would love their range of pizzas and their taste if you like thin crush pizzas - like the Mexican nachos one myself. Drinks are good too with offers - mainly people opt for Bira. Had sizzling Brownie in desserts and it was yum! Can improve more on overall crust and taste of the pizzas though - not that nice if you're going only for food.   Visited during lunch hours.

  This restaurant was a big disappointment. The list of unprofessionalism is quite big.
We found a dead cockroach near the table. And when pointing it out the service guy was least bothered and asked some other guy to look into it.Then we shifted to a different table.
Another downer was the unresponsive attitude of the staff. We literally had to get up from our seats to give order.
The food was above par to it's service, which was a good thing. But when some one visits ur restaurant, they want to have the full dining experience. Otherwise food can be home delivered.
Please work on ur cleanliness and service if u want to attract customers."), ('Rated 5.0', 'RATED

column2: 136, SAP Labs India, KIADB Export Promotion Industrial Area, Whitefield, Bangalore
column3: The Farm House Bar n Grill
column14:
[('Rated 4.0', 'RATED
  Ambience- Big and spacious lawn was used to host new year event including unlimited food, drinks, dj, dholak performance, firedance and belly dance.

Pocket friendly- Reasonable for the services offered.

Food- Veg and Non veg starters were served hot and had plenty of options including Fish and Chicken. The dishes could have been less oily.

In drinks you had plenty of options for alcoholic drinks but only 3 non alcoholic drinks which was dissapointing.

Main course had good variety of Breads, Salads, Rice Items, Curries in both veg and nonveg. Desserts had plenty of options to choose from apart from the regular ones.

Service- Quick and prompt considering the crowd. The bar could have been better managed for non alcoholic section.

Rating- 4 for the awsome experience.')]
